(64, 3, 1, 'Statement 1: Taxation and Police power may be exercised simultaneously\r\nStatement 2: In the exercise of taxation, the State can tax anything and anytime and at any amount.', 'Government can exercised the three powers of the state simultaneously.\r\n\r\nThe Power of Taxation is broad, powerful and unlimited. But even though it is said to be unlimited, it is subject to Inherent and Constitutional limitations.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 17:47:54', '2020-12-09 17:47:54'),
(65, 3, 1, 'Statement 1: The power of taxation must be first expressly granted, either by law or by the Constitution, before the State may validly exercise it.\r\nStatement 2: The Philippine gov’t may subject the land where embassies of foreign gov’ts are located to real property taxes.', 'Power of taxation is inherent, therefore it does need to be granted by the Constitution.\r\nThe Government can’t tax or subject to tax its own property or properties stated in Special Treaty or Agreement with other foreign countries. And even properties beyond the territorial jurisdiction of the government are not subject to tax.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 17:49:01', '2020-12-09 17:49:01'),
