(67, 3, 1, 'Statement 1: Since taxation presupposes an equivalent from compensation, there should be a direct and proximate advantage received by any taxpayer before he could be required to pay tax.\r\nStatement 2: Compensation under police power is the intangible feeling of contribution to the general welfare of the people.', 'Taxation is for public purpose in general, it is based on Fiscal Adequacy Theory and not on benefit-received theory', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:34:01', '2020-12-09 18:34:01'),
(68, 3, 1, 'Which of the inherent powers maybe exercised even by the public utility companies?', 'Government only can exercise the power of taxation and police, but public utility company may exercise the power of eminent domain.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:34:59', '2020-12-09 18:34:59'),
