(70, 3, 1, 'Statement 1: Police power and the power of taxation are exercised primarily by the legislature but not eminent domain.\r\nStatement 2: Taxation and eminent domain interferes with private right and property but no with police power.', 'All the 3 inherent powers of the State are legislative in application\r\nAll the 3 inherent powers interfere with private rights and property. However, the police power of the State interferes with private/property rights and liberty.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:36:19', '2020-12-09 18:36:19'),
(71, 3, 1, 'The existence of the government is a necessity and that the state has the right to compel all individual and property within its limits to contribute.', 'Fiscal Adequacy is the principle behind the power of the government to collect taxes, at any amount, anything at any time, so long as the government needs funds for the public purpose. To maintain its existence and to defray all its expenses, the government does collect from individuals and property with-in its jurisdiction. Also, the theory spawned in the Doctrine of Symbiotic Relationship which means, taxes are what we pay for a civilized society.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:39:07', '2020-12-09 18:39:07'),
(72, 3, 1, 'Which statement below expresses the lifeblood theory?', 'Taxes are said to be the lifeblood of the government. For it to continue its existence, it needs to collect taxes adequate for its expenses.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:39:43', '2020-12-09 18:39:43'),
(73, 3, 1, 'The principal purpose of taxation is:', 'The very essence of taxation is to raise revenue to defray the expenses of the government.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:40:36', '2020-12-09 18:40:36'),
(74, 3, 1, 'After the report and series of investigations that all of the registered Karaoke Bars in the City of Dagupan have done violations on the moral law of the city concerning prostitutions and some ordinances of the city, the City Government has imposed within its territorial jurisdiction to such an “onerous tax” that leave them no other alternatives but to stop the operations of the said bars. The passage of the ordinance is a valid exercise of-', 'The legislative branch of the LGU passed a “tax ordinance”, a valid exercise of the LGU’s power to tax. However, the main purpose of the tax ordinance was not to raise revenue but to impede the progress of illegal karaoke, a valid exercise of police power through taxation.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:41:05', '2020-12-09 18:41:05'),
(75, 3, 1, 'Statement 1. A provision on taxation in the Philippines Constitution is a grant power.\r\nStatement 2. The power to tax includes the power to destroy.\r\nStatement 3. Sumptuary purpose of taxation is to raise funds for the government.', 'Constitutional provisions on taxations are merely limitations in the exercise off the power of taxation by the State.\r\nSumptuary purpose refers to non – revenue purpose, hence, no to raise fund for the government.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:42:35', '2020-12-09 18:42:35'),
(76, 3, 1, 'A tax must be imposed for a public purpose. Which of the following is not a public purpose?', 'Determination of the purpose of imposition\r\n“It is not the immediate result but the ultimate result that determines, whether the purpose is public or not.  It is not the number of persons benefited but it is the character of the purpose that determines the public character of such law. What is not allowed is that, if it has no link to public welfare. Public purpose determined by the use to which the tax money is devoted. If it benefits the community in general, then it is for public purpose no matter who collects it” (Tio vs. Videgram).', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:43:26', '2020-12-09 18:43:26'),
(77, 3, 1, 'The levying and imposition of the tax and the collection of the tax are processes which constitute the taxation system', 'these are the stages or aspects of taxation 1.Levy–This refers to the enactment of a law by Congress imposing a tax 2.Assessment and collection–This is the act of administration and implementation of the tax law by the executive branch through the administrative agencies 3.Payment–This is the act of compliance by the tax payer including whatever remedies are available to him under the law', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:44:11', '2020-12-09 18:44:11'),
(78, 3, 1, 'The following are the aspect of taxation\r\nI- Levying or imposition if the tax in persons, property or excises\r\nII- Collection of taxes already levied\r\nIII- Sufficiency of governments sources to satisfy its expenditure', 'these are the stages or aspects of taxation 1.Levy–This refers to the enactment of a law by Congress imposing a tax 2.Assessment and collection–This is the act of administration and implementation of the tax law by the executive branch through the administrative agencies 3.Payment–This is the act of compliance by the tax payer including whatever remedies are available to him under the law', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:45:10', '2020-12-09 18:45:10'),
(79, 3, 1, 'The official action of an officer authorized by law in ascertaining the amount of tax due under the law form a taxpayer is', 'The Government has the power to assessed the value or even the amount of tax or the amount of property to be taxed or to be imposed.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:45:54', '2020-12-09 18:45:54'),
(80, 3, 1, 'Taxation is exercised both by the legislative and executive branch of the gov’t. Which of the following is not function of the Congress?', 'It is the executive branch who is in-charged in the execution of the laws of taxation from assessment to collections.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:46:51', '2020-12-09 18:46:51'),
(81, 3, 1, 'Fixing the tax rate to be imposed is best described as a (an):', 'Fixing the rate to be imposed is still part of levying stage of taxation, in which levying is given to Congress, therefore it is legislative function.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:47:23', '2020-12-09 18:47:23'),
(82, 3, 1, 'All of the following are legislative aspect of taxation except', '2nd stage of taxation is assessment and collection which were given to executive branch. Valuation of the property for taxation is part of assessment process and therefore it is not a legislative function but rather under executive function.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:47:58', '2020-12-09 18:47:58'),
(83, 3, 1, 'All of the following are administrative functions of taxation except', 'Levying is a legislative function and it includes the determination of tax rates and the items and objects to be subjected to tax. The selection of object therefore is a legislative function.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:49:02', '2020-12-09 18:49:02'),
(84, 3, 1, 'The Commissioner of Internal Revenue is granted certain powers under the Tax Code. Which of the following is not a power granted to the Commissioner under the Code?', 'Enactment and amendments are legislative in nature, therefore these are not powers of the executive branch specifically the BIR Commissioner.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:51:15', '2020-12-09 18:51:15'),
(85, 3, 1, 'Which of the following statement is correct?', 'The BIR Commissioner shall have the power to interpret lax laws but subject to the approval of the Secretary of Finance. The commission shall have one commissioner and several deputy commissioners ( there were times when there are four deputy commissioners and times when there are more than four deputy commissioners.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:51:50', '2020-12-09 18:51:50'),
