(87, 3, 1, 'How will the local gov’t units be able to exercise their taxing powers?', 'Local Government Units ( province, city or municipality and barangay) could impose tax laws thru local legislation. For the provincial level, it is the Provincial Board Members and Vice Governor who compose the Sangguniang Panlalawigan, for municipal and city, the councilors and vice mayor, and for barangay are the barangay officials.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:53:13', '2020-12-09 18:53:13'),
(88, 3, 1, 'When is the power to tax, be delegated to the local government units?', 'The aspects of taxation (levying, assessment, and collection) in the national level is also applicable to the power of taxation by the LGUs.\r\nLevying = local legislative branch\r\nAssessment and collection = local executive branch', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:56:39', '2020-12-09 18:56:39'),
(89, 3, 1, 'Levying of local government taxes may be exercised by:', 'Levying function can be exercised by the legislative branch of the local government unit only and also the 2nd and 3rd stages which assessment and collection and payments are for executive branch of the LGU only.', 'easy', 30, '2020-12-09 18:57:22', '2020-12-09 18:57:22'),
