(730, 18, 1, 'This is the process or method whereby accusations are brought before the court of justice to determine the innocence or guilt of the accused:', 'trial', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:35:06', '2021-01-19 16:35:38'),
(731, 17, 1, 'A home health nurse who is following an 88-year-old patient with severe hypertension in addition to his respiratory problem notices several drugs on the bedside table. The medication that the nurse would suggest the patient avoid is:', 'Decongestants increase the blood pressure.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:35:07', '2021-01-19 16:35:07'),
(733, 17, 1, 'To enhance gas exchange, the nurse would position a patient who had a left pneumonectomy this morning:', 'Elevation of the head helps gas exchange in a new pneumonectomy. Complete side-lying on the unaffected side may cause mediastinal shift', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:35:49', '2021-01-19 16:35:49'),
(734, 17, 1, 'A patient with acute bronchitis is being discharged with a prescription for an antimicrobial to be taken for the next 14 days. In the discharge teaching, the nurse will stress:', 'The entire course of the prescription should be taken to destroy the pathogen completely; otherwise, the pathogen may become resistant to the drug.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:36:32', '2021-01-19 16:36:32'),
(735, 18, 1, 'This quantum of evidence refers the set of probabilities grounded in the factual and practical considerations which govern the decisions of reasonable and prudent persons and is more than mere suspicion:', 'b.	probable cause', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:37:42', '2021-01-19 16:37:42'),
(736, 18, 1, 'This refers to the process of dispute resolution in which a neutral third party renders a decision after a hearing at which both parties have an opportunity to be heard:', 'arbitration', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:39:11', '2021-01-19 16:39:11'),
(737, 18, 1, 'This is the power and authority of the court to hear, try and decide cases:', 'jurisdiction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:41:12', '2021-01-19 16:41:12'),
(738, 18, 1, 'This power includes the duty of the court to settle actual controversies involving rights which are legally demandable and enforceable and to determine whether or not there has been a grave abuse of discretion amounting to lack or excess of jurisdiction on the part of the any branch or instrumentalities of the government:', 'judicial power', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:42:34', '2021-01-19 16:42:34'),
(739, 18, 1, 'The power or right conferred upon by law of acting officially in certain circumstances according to the dictates of their own judgment or conscience, uncontrolled by the judgment or conscience of others is largely practiced by this player in the Criminal Justice System:', 'police', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 16:43:17', '2021-01-19 16:43:17'),
(740, 17, 1, 'The group that the nurse would advise to have a vaccination with conjugated pneumococcal vaccine is:', 'The conjugated product is especially designed for young children. Unconjugated vaccine is recommended for older adults and persons with cardiovascular disorders', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:06:33', '2021-01-19 17:06:33'),
(741, 17, 1, 'To reduce the risk of aspiration in a patient who is receiving enteral feedings running at 70 mL/hour, the nurse should:', 'A residual of over 20% of the hourly rate should be reported so that the rate can be reduced', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:08:05', '2021-01-19 17:08:05'),
(742, 17, 1, 'The symptoms of hypoxemia for which the nurse should be alert are:', 'The universal symptoms of hypoxemia, regardless of cause, are restlessness, tachycardia, and tachypnea.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:09:00', '2021-01-19 17:09:00'),
(743, 17, 1, 'A patient comes to the ER with a sucking chest wound. Which type of dressing should the nurse apply to begin the process of lung reinflation?', 'The flutter dressing occludes air from entering but allows air to escape, avoiding a tension pneumothorax and mediastinal shift.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:09:41', '2021-01-19 17:09:41'),
(744, 18, 1, 'This process intends to determine whether the accused could have committed the crime charged:', 'Preliminary Investigation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:10:14', '2021-01-19 17:10:14'),
(745, 18, 1, 'The presentation of sufficient facts as would convince the judge issuing the warrant or arrest, not that the particular person has committed the crime, but that there is a sufficient reason for believing that the person whose arrest is sought, committed the crime charged:', 'Probable cause', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:11:02', '2021-01-19 17:11:02'),
(746, 17, 1, 'When the nurse observes the paradoxical movement in a patient with a flail chest who has marked dyspnea, the nurse should prepare for:', 'A patient with an unstable chest usually requires intubation and mechanical ventilation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:11:04', '2021-01-19 17:11:04'),
(747, 17, 1, 'The intervention that would be inappropriate for decreasing the risk of further emboli in a patient with a pulmonary embolism is:', 'Nothing should be placed under the knees, where circulation might be impaired.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:12:18', '2021-01-19 17:12:18'),
(748, 18, 1, 'This unit, which is under the Department of Justice is composed of the Office of the Chief State Prosecutor, Regional State Prosecution Offices, and the Provincial and City Prosecution Offices, serve as the principal prosecutory arm of the government under the helm of the Secretary of Justice:', 'NPS', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:15:23', '2021-01-19 17:15:23'),
(749, 19, 1, 'The nurse performs an apical-radial pulse evaluation, with the result of 100/88. This pulse deficit assessment is:', 'To detect an apical radial pulse deficit, the rates should be counted simultaneously and compared for differences. If there is a difference between the apical rate and radial rate, a pulse deficit is present. For example, in atrial fibrillation, a pulse deficit exists.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:15:47', '2021-01-19 17:15:47'),
(750, 18, 1, 'This is primarily tasked for the expeditious delivery of prosecutorial services in ordinary criminal cases:', 'NPS', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:16:15', '2021-01-19 17:16:15'),
(751, 19, 1, 'The nurse explains that hypertension increases the work of the heart because of increasing:', 'An increase blood pressure creates an increase in afterload because the heart must work harder to push the blood out of the left ventricle into the circulating volume.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:16:27', '2021-01-19 17:16:27'),
(752, 18, 1, 'This is an informal and summary investigation conducted by a public prosecutor in criminal cases involving persons arrested and detained without the benefit of a warrant of arrest issued by the court for the purpose of determining whether or not said persons should remain under custody and correspondingly be charged in court:', 'Inquest', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:17:10', '2021-01-19 17:17:10'),
(753, 18, 1, 'This jurisdiction empowers the court to decide all disputes, which may come before it except those assigned to other courts:', 'General', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:17:50', '2021-01-19 17:17:50'),
(754, 18, 1, 'This is an order in writing issued in the name of the People of the Philippines, signed by a judge and directed to a peace officer, commanding him to search for personal property described therein and bring it before the court:', 'Search Warrant', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:18:37', '2021-01-19 17:18:37'),
(755, 18, 1, 'This principal character of the criminal justice process links all components of the CJS:', 'Offender', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:19:16', '2021-01-19 17:19:16'),
(756, 19, 1, 'The heart sound the nurse would record as normal would be:', 'Ventricular gallops are considered normal in persons under 30. All other options are pathologic', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:19:49', '2021-01-19 17:19:49'),
(757, 18, 1, 'The front line defender of democracy in the CJS:', 'Court', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:20:07', '2021-01-19 17:20:07'),
(758, 19, 1, 'A 49-year-old patient has multiple risk factors for coronary artery disease. A modifiable risk factor that the patient can focus on is:', 'Smoking, a high-fat diet, hypertension, sedentary lifestyle, and stress are considered modifiable risk factors', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:20:24', '2021-01-19 17:20:24'),
(759, 18, 1, 'It consists the ordering of human relations in accordance with general principles impartially applied:', 'Justice', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:20:55', '2021-01-19 17:20:55'),
(760, 19, 1, 'When the patient asks what a TEE is and what it is expected to do, the nurse explains that the TEE is a transesophageal echocardiogram, which:', 'A TEE evaluates the valve efficiency.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:21:31', '2021-01-19 17:21:31'),
(761, 19, 1, 'The nurse records the finding of normal sinus rhythm (NSR) when the P, Q, R, S, and T are all present in the electrocardiographic complex and a(an):', 'NSR requires the presence of P, Q, R, S, and T waves, in that order, and all pointing in the same direction, with a rate of 80 to 100. Normal intervals are PR, 0.12 to 0.20 second, QRS, less than 0.10 second.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:39:33', '2021-01-19 17:39:33'),
(762, 19, 1, 'The nurse would anticipate that a patient on Vasotec (ACE inhibitor) would have as a positive outcome to this drug:', 'ACE inhibitors suppress the excretion of angiotensin, which lowers the blood pressure, reduces fluid retention, and leads to increased urine output.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:41:13', '2021-01-19 17:41:13'),
(763, 19, 1, 'A 29-year-old patient is to receive cardioversion for his dysrhythmia. The nurse will instruct the patient to expect:', 'Cardioversions have risks, such as ventricular fibrillation. Emergency equipment should be available. The digoxin dose is held before a cardioversion and the patient is given a short-acting sedative such as Versed or Valium, which will require recovery. The electrocardiogram R wave is synchronized via computer, and there is no pacemaker involved.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:41:54', '2021-01-19 17:41:54'),
(765, 19, 1, 'A 68-year-old patient is scheduled for open heart surgery in the morning and is crying. The appropriate response from the nurse would be:', 'Therapeutic implementations identify and acknowledge feelings. Do not assume that you know how the patient feels and do not give false reassurance.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:42:58', '2021-01-19 17:42:58'),
(766, 18, 1, 'He is responsible for evaluating the traces the police have gathered and deciding whether it is sufficient to warrant the filing of charge(s) against the alleged violator:', 'Prosecutor', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:43:13', '2021-01-19 17:43:13'),
(767, 19, 1, 'The nurse explains that when fibrous plaques of atherosclerosis are laid down in the vessels, they serve as a(an):', 'The plaque surface acts as a trap to which fibrous plaques can adhere, causing more narrowing of the vessel. The enlarging plaque can become a thrombus, but not an embolus, because emboli usually are considered to be traveling aggregations that lodge in a small arteriole.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:43:50', '2021-01-19 17:43:50'),
(768, 18, 1, 'He conducts pre-sentence investigation which the judge will make use of in the determination of sentence:', 'Probation officer', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:44:04', '2021-01-19 17:44:04'),
(769, 18, 1, 'He is an arbitrator in court who ensures that the defense and the prosecution adhere to the legal requirements of the introducing evidences:', 'Judge', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:44:44', '2021-01-19 17:44:44'),
(770, 19, 1, 'A patient with an irregular SA node conduction has a permanent pacemaker with the code “A A I O O” and now is going home. The patient asks, “What happens when my real SA node fires on its own?” The nurse responds that the pacemaker will:', 'The code is A (chamber-paced) atria, A (sense impulse) atria only, I (inhibit) inhibit firing from pacemaker, O (rate modification) no rate modification, O (multichamber) no other chambers to be stimulated by the pacemaker. If the SA fires on its own, the pacemaker does nothing until it fails to sense an impulse', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:44:45', '2021-01-19 17:44:45'),
(771, 18, 1, 'This is known as the Police Professionalization Act of 1966, which also created the Police Commission (Polcom), later renamed as the National Police Commission:', 'RA 4864', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:45:39', '2021-01-19 17:45:39'),
(772, 19, 1, 'When the angina pectoris patient complains of chest pain at rest that takes three nitroglycerin (NTG) pills to relieve, the nurse assesses this as a major symptom of:', 'An angina patient who has pain at rest that is not relieved with only one NTG is considered to have unstable angina, a precursor to an acute MI.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:45:50', '2021-01-19 17:45:50'),
(773, 18, 1, 'This government institution has a direct administrative supervision and control over the Philippine National Police Academy (PNPA):', 'Philippine Public Safety College', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:46:24', '2021-01-19 17:46:24'),
(774, 19, 1, 'The nurse explains that cardiac rehabilitation lasts from the end of acute care to the return home and beyond. This service includes:', 'Cardiac rehabilitation programs are supervised by a team of experts who arrange for telemetry-supervised exercise and other modalities, such as diet and medical protocol management. The focus is on the family as well as the patient and, although some patients reject the program, they are very rarely rejected by the rehabilitation center.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:46:32', '2021-01-19 17:46:32'),
(775, 18, 1, 'This is otherwise known as, “The Integrated National Police Personnel Professionalization Law of 1977:', 'PD 765', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:47:08', '2021-01-19 17:47:08');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `lesson_id`, `enabled`, `question_text`, `justification`, `difficulty`, `time`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(776, 19, 1, 'On auscultation, the nurse detects a heart murmur. The nurse knows that a heart murmur indicates:', 'Heart murmurs indicate turbulent blood flow and can be caused by valves that are stiff and do not shut correctly, so that blood is flowing back into the chamber.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:47:14', '2021-01-19 17:47:14'),
(777, 19, 1, 'An important teaching point for a patient with mitral stenosis is to:', 'Patients with mitral stenosis need to take care to balance their activity with their oxygen supply and not to overhydrate themselves.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:47:55', '2021-01-19 17:47:55'),
(778, 19, 1, 'The physician has ordered continuous pulse oximetry. The nurse explains to the patient that the procedure:', 'Pulse oximetry measures arterial oxygen saturation noninvasively by attaching a clip to a digit, ear, or nose.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:48:32', '2021-01-19 17:48:32'),
(779, 18, 1, 'The qualifying and promotional examination of police applicants and PNP personnel shall be administered by:', 'Napolcom', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:48:53', '2021-01-19 17:48:53'),
(780, 19, 1, 'A stress test is scheduled for a 41-year-old patient. To prepare for the examination, the nurse would:', 'A stress test is a noninvasive test that consists of a patient walking on a treadmill while an electrocardiogram (ECG) recording is done. A consent form is required.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:49:15', '2021-01-19 17:49:15'),
(781, 18, 1, '“An Act Providing for the Organization and Government of an Insular Constabulary,” is:', 'Act # 175', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:49:45', '2021-01-19 17:49:45'),
(782, 19, 1, 'When a patient returns from a cardiac catheterization, the nurse would expect to:', 'Cardiac catheterizations are invasive procedures in which a catheter is threaded through an artery. Postprocedure care requires bed rest and monitoring puncture sites.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:49:58', '2021-01-19 17:49:58'),
(783, 18, 1, 'As provided in the 1987 Constitution, what should be the scope of the  police force?', 'National', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:50:42', '2021-01-19 17:50:42'),
(784, 19, 1, 'When the nurse assesses an inverted T wave on the ECG of a patient who is 2 days post–acute MI, the nurse interprets this as ____ of the myocardium.', 'The inverted T wave is an indicator that there has been tissue death in part of the cardiac wall. It now has no ability to conduct or to contract and sends that message to the ECG via the inverted T. The tissue will take 6 weeks to regenerate.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:50:44', '2021-01-19 17:50:44'),
(785, 19, 1, 'Laboratory tests are performed to identify damage to the heart muscle. The test that is elevated the earliest with heart damage is:', 'Troponin is elevated within 2 to 6 hours and is often measured in the emergency department. CPK-MB is elevated in 12 to 24 hours. Three serial samples are drawn. The LDH increases with heart damage within 3 to 6 days. The lipid profile is not elevated with heart damage.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:51:38', '2021-01-19 17:51:38'),
(786, 18, 1, 'P.D. 765, otherwise known as the Integration Act of 1975, has also transferred the Napolcom from the Office of the President to what agency?', 'MND', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:51:54', '2021-01-19 17:51:54'),
(787, 19, 1, 'A patient is scheduled for a heart catheterization. In preparation for this examination, the nurse would:', 'The dye injected during the cardiac catheterization is iodine-based. An allergy to seafood is correlated with a reaction to this dye as well.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:52:38', '2021-01-19 17:52:38'),
(788, 18, 1, 'An attached agency to the DILG for policy and program coordination on matters affecting law and order:', 'Napolcom', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:52:47', '2021-01-19 17:52:47'),
(789, 19, 1, 'To treat a dysrhythmia, atropine sulfate has been administered intravenously. The nurse would monitor for:', 'Atropine increases heart rate. The nurse should watch for tachycardia, which increases the workload of the heart. This medication causes urinary retention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:53:11', '2021-01-19 17:53:11'),
(790, 18, 1, 'This system refers to the orderly progression of events from the time a person is arrested, investigated, prosecuted, sentenced, rehabilitated and eventually returned to the community:', 'Criminal Justice System', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:53:32', '2021-01-19 17:53:32'),
(791, 18, 1, 'The precursor of the National Bureau of Investigation (NBI):', 'Division of Investigation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:54:25', '2021-01-19 17:54:25'),
(792, 18, 1, 'This is defined as the regular procedure followed in the administration of law:', 'Due process of law', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:55:06', '2021-01-19 17:55:06'),
(793, 18, 1, 'This the governmental body which is charged with the responsibility of administering justice:', 'Court', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:55:41', '2021-01-19 17:55:41'),
(794, 18, 1, 'Any person directly vested with jurisdiction, whether as an individual or as a member of some court, government corporation, board or commission:', 'Agent of person in authority', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:56:29', '2021-01-19 17:56:29'),
(795, 18, 1, 'The machinery of the state or government which enforces the rules of conduct necessary to protect life and property and to maintain law and order:', 'Criminal Justice System', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:57:09', '2021-01-19 17:57:09'),
(796, 19, 1, 'A dopamine infusion is being administered to a patient with shock. The nurse should be alert for:', 'Dopamine has a direct effect by elevating the blood pressure. The criterion is to titrate to the target blood pressure. Urinary output should also be monitored for a decreased amount, because a heightened blood pressure may slow urine filtration and reduce urine output.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:57:19', '2021-01-19 17:57:19'),
(797, 19, 1, 'The patient with atrial fibrillation is placed on amiodarone for the dysrhythmia. The nurse should report the adverse reaction of:', 'The drug amiodarone is meant to quiet atrial activity and modify rapid pulse rate, high blood pressure, and decreased cardiac output caused by the dysrhythmia. The drug interferes with the thyroid and will cause an ataxic gait and trembling of hands as adverse effects.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:58:35', '2021-01-19 17:58:35'),
(798, 19, 1, 'A medication, simvastatin (Zocor), is administered to lower a patient’s cholesterol level. Follow-up lipid levels are reviewed by the nurse. The level that indicates the desired therapeutic range is:', 'The reading that has both an HDL level above 40 mg/dL and an LDL level below 100 mg/dL is in the therapeutic target range.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:59:20', '2021-01-19 17:59:20'),
(799, 18, 1, 'Basically, a police department is organized first and foremost from this purpose:', 'Crime prevention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 17:59:39', '2021-01-19 17:59:39'),
(800, 19, 1, 'A patient has had an acute MI. The nurse should include in the discharge instructions:', 'The patient needs written instructions for diet, follow-up appointments, and exercise protocols. Giving detailed information about symptoms is not necessary, other than to remind about reporting chest pain and shortness of breath. A high-energy exercise program is not appropriate. Morphine is not part of the home care of a post-MI.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:00:14', '2021-01-19 18:00:14'),
(801, 18, 1, 'This embraces crime prevention and crime control role, including the customary police functions:', 'Law enforcement', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:00:23', '2021-01-19 18:00:23'),
(802, 19, 1, 'A patient with acute congestive heart failure presents with jugular vein distention, crackles bilaterally, and dyspnea. The nursing diagnosis with the highest priority would be:', 'Fluid volume excess increases the workload of the heart and interferes with breathing.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:01:04', '2021-01-19 18:01:04'),
(803, 18, 1, 'An act or omission of one party in violation of the legal rights of the other for which the latter suffers damage or prejudice and the existence of which affords a party to a right of judicial interference or intervention on his behalf:', 'Cause of action', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:01:13', '2021-01-19 18:01:13'),
(804, 18, 1, 'This is the process or method whereby accusations are brought before the court of justice to determine the innocence or guilt of the accused:', 'Prosecution', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:01:54', '2021-01-19 18:01:54'),
(805, 19, 1, 'A patient has acute congestive heart failure. A nursing intervention to decrease the workload of the heart would be to:', 'Group activities allow for adequate rest. The patient should be placed in a high Fowler’s position, and small or no meals are offered.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:02:38', '2021-01-19 18:02:38'),
(806, 18, 1, 'The Act defining certain rights of the person arrested, detained or under custodial investigation, as well as the duties of the arresting, detaining, and investigating officers, and providing penalties for violation thereof:', 'RA 7438', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:02:46', '2021-01-19 18:02:46'),
(807, 19, 1, 'A diuretic medication is being administered for congestive heart failure. The nurse should monitor for an adverse effect of:', 'Increased urinary output, weight loss, and thirst are all anticipated consequences of the therapy. Muscle weakness is a sign of hypokalemia.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:03:35', '2021-01-19 18:03:35'),
(808, 18, 1, 'It embraces any activity in the community directly aimed at helping the offender to become a law abiding citizen?', 'Community-based correction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:03:53', '2021-01-19 18:03:53'),
(809, 19, 1, 'A patient is receiving digoxin, 0.25 mg daily. Before giving the medication, the nurse would:', 'The dose should be held if the apical rate is less than 60 beats/min for 1 minute.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:04:21', '2021-01-19 18:04:21'),
(810, 18, 1, 'This document is required by the Prosecutor’s Office before it can entertain a complaint on a case covered by the Barangay Court:', 'Certificate to File Action', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:04:38', '2021-01-19 18:04:38'),
(811, 19, 1, 'A 46-year-old patient is receiving propranolol (Inderal), a nonselective beta-adrenergic blocker for his heart condition. The nurse would teach the patient to:', 'Beta-blockers should never be stopped abruptly because they can cause angina or a myocardial infarction. Patients are gradually weaned off these medications.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:05:02', '2021-01-19 18:05:02'),
(812, 19, 1, 'The nurse caring for a patient on lidocaine to increase ventricular conduction is alarmed when assessments reveal:', 'A temperature rate that goes up drastically indicates an adverse reaction to lidocaine, malignant hyperthermia. The slowed ventricular rate, even with occasional PVCs, is an expected outcome of lidocaine infusion.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:05:34', '2021-01-19 18:05:34'),
(813, 18, 1, 'Who determines the members of the Lupon:', 'Barangay Captain', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:06:01', '2021-01-19 18:06:01'),
(814, 18, 1, 'It is that branch in the administration of criminal justice which is charged with the responsibility for the custody, supervision, and rehabilitation of the convicted offenders:', 'Corrections', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:06:41', '2021-01-19 18:06:41'),
(815, 18, 1, 'To sit en banc means to sit:', 'as one body', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:07:38', '2021-01-19 18:07:38'),
(816, 19, 1, 'The nurse takes a blood pressure with the 65-year-old patient lying down and then again with the patient standing, with the resultant readings of 152/92 and 130/62. The nurse should record:', 'A difference of more than a 20 mm Hg between lying and standing BP is an indicator of orthostatic postural hypotension.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:07:55', '2021-01-19 18:07:55'),
(817, 18, 1, '51.	This type of jurisdiction refers to the authority to hear and determine only a few specified cases:', 'Limited', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:08:15', '2021-01-19 18:08:15'),
(818, 19, 1, 'The nurse records a 1 for the pulse quality of the pedal pulse. This means that the pulse is:', 'A 1 in a pulse evaluation indicates a thready pulse that is easily obliterated by pressure.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:08:38', '2021-01-19 18:08:38'),
(819, 18, 1, '52.	He is tasked with the delicate task of developing criminal actions and other proceedings for violation(s) of law(s):', 'Prosecutor', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:08:57', '2021-01-19 18:08:57'),
(820, 18, 1, 'This is the period given to the Barangay Chairman, from the start of his term, to constitute a Lupon:', '15 days', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:09:49', '2021-01-19 18:09:49'),
(821, 18, 1, 'This is an act of the sovereign power granting general pardon for a past offense usually granted in favor of certain classes of persons who have committed crimes of a political character, such as treason, sedition or rebellion:', 'Amnesty', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:10:27', '2021-01-19 18:10:27'),
(822, 20, 1, 'The nurse assesses wheezes in a patient with asthma and realizes that these breath sounds result from:', 'Wheezes are adventitious sounds made by air passing through narrowed passages', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-19 18:10:38', '2021-01-19 18:10:38'),
