(924, 20, 1, 'The COPD patient has a nursing diagnosis of “Activity intolerance related to inability to meet oxygen needs.” The intervention that would be inappropriate for this diagnosis would be:', 'Bunching nursing activities is tiring to the patient with COPD. Assisting only when needed saves patient energy as well as enhancing independence. Activities should be spread out to allow for uninterrupted rest periods. Progressive ambulation is an acceptable way to build tolerance.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:19:32', '2021-01-20 16:19:32'),
(925, 20, 1, 'The nurse recognizes that a rising PaCO2 level in a COPD patient means that', 'A rising PaCO2 level (arterial carbon dioxide pressure) is acidic in nature and causes respiratory acidosis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:20:18', '2021-01-20 16:20:18'),
(926, 20, 1, 'The nurse is aware that the characteristic of emphysema that gives rise to the “Pink Puffer” label is the emphysemic patient’s:', 'The normal ABGs give the emphysemic patient a normal pink color, rather than cyanosed, like the Blue Bloater', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:22:19', '2021-01-20 16:22:19'),
(927, 18, 1, 'A body officially assembled under authority of law in which judicial power is vested or the administration of justice is delegated.', 'Court', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:27:10', '2021-01-20 16:27:10'),
(928, 18, 1, 'Mandated by law to bring to justice all criminal cases for action and prove the guilt of the accused beyond reasonable doubt.', 'Prosecution', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:27:40', '2021-01-20 16:27:40'),
(929, 18, 1, 'A body of civil authority tasked to maintain peace and order, enforce the law, protect life, liberty and property and ensure public safety.', 'Police', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:28:08', '2021-01-20 16:28:08'),
(930, 18, 1, 'System of taking care of the custody, rehabilitation and treatment of persons convicted of committing a crime.', 'Corrections', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:28:41', '2021-01-20 16:28:41'),
(931, 18, 1, 'The Anti Graft and Corrupt Practices Act.', 'RA 3019', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:29:08', '2021-01-20 16:29:08'),
(932, 20, 1, 'The COPD patient asks the nurse if nicotine patches are effective for smoking cessation. The nurse’s best response would be:', 'The patches have a lower than 25% success rate. Smoking addiction is too strong to be overcome by medication or gum without very unusual commitment from the patient. Successful smoking cessation is measured by 1 year of no smoking.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:29:30', '2021-01-20 16:29:30'),
(933, 18, 1, 'Law which created the National Bureau of Investigations.', 'RA 157', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:29:37', '2021-01-20 16:29:37'),
(934, 20, 1, 'The cystic fibrosis patient furiously refuses any more manual chest physiotherapy. The nurse could suggest which alternative?', 'A flutter mucus clearance device is a hand-held vibrating tool that helps loosen and evacuate secretions in the lung.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:30:49', '2021-01-20 16:30:49'),
(935, 18, 1, 'The agency under the Department of Finance tasked to enforce tariff duties in all Philippine seaports and airports.', 'Bureau of Customs', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:31:23', '2021-01-20 16:31:23'),
(936, 20, 1, 'The nurse assessing the CBC of a patient with chronic bronchitis identifies a typical feature of this disease, which is:', 'Chronic bronchitis patients show a large increase of red blood cells with an attendant higher hemoglobin level, because they must produce more RBCs for the transport of O2. Frequently, the WBCs are elevated because of the chronic inflammation. Decreased levels of platelets and eosinophils are indicative of pathology other than bronchitis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:31:35', '2021-01-20 16:31:35'),
(937, 20, 1, 'The COPD patient delightedly tells the nurse that he has quit smoking and is using chewing tobacco. The nurse’s best intervention would be to:', 'Smokeless tobacco has adverse effects, including oral cancer.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:32:20', '2021-01-20 16:32:20'),
(938, 18, 1, 'The Bureau of Immigration and Deportation, which is tasked to enforce Philippine Immigration Laws, is an attached agency of:', 'Department of Justice', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:33:10', '2021-01-20 16:33:10'),
(939, 20, 1, 'A newly diagnosed patient with squamous cell lung carcinoma (SCLC) is anxious about having to take chemotherapy. The intervention by the nurse that would be helpful is to:', 'Surgery is the treatment of choice of SCLC carcinomas. Options 2 and 3 are not correct, because SCLC tumors are sometimes treated by chemotherapy and radiation before or after surgery. The survival rate is only about 14%. Although referral may be in the long-range plan, the patient’s need is immediate for information that is in the scope of nursing.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:33:13', '2021-01-20 16:33:13'),
(940, 18, 1, 'It regulates marine and shipping industry and oversees the worthiness of all sea-going vessels.', 'Maritime Industry Authority (MARINA)', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:33:44', '2021-01-20 16:33:44'),
(941, 20, 1, 'The theophylline blood level is 13 mcg/mL. Which intervention is the most appropriate in light of this finding?', 'The therapeutic range of theophylline is 5 to 15 mcg/mL. The drug should be administered. This drug is not the drug of choice today but is still in use, even though it causes cardiac problems.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:34:03', '2021-01-20 16:34:03'),
(942, 18, 1, 'It is mandated by law to operate against fake and pirated VHS, VCD, CD and DVD format tapes.', 'Video Gram Regulatory Board', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:34:12', '2021-01-20 16:34:12'),
(943, 18, 1, 'The Intellectual Property office which is mandated to operate against the violations of the copy right and intellectual property law is under the:', 'Department of Trade and Industry', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:34:40', '2021-01-20 16:34:40'),
(944, 18, 1, 'It investigates and arrests unscrupulous manufacturers and makers of substandard food and drugs without license and permit.', 'Bureau of Food and Drugs', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:35:09', '2021-01-20 16:35:09'),
(945, 18, 1, 'The Bureau of Quarantine is empowered to enforce measures to stop, monitor and control the spread of disease by conducting quarantine in all air and seaports across the country is an attached agency of:', 'DOH', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:36:30', '2021-01-20 16:36:30'),
(946, 18, 1, 'It operates against pornography films shown on television and movie houses.', 'Movie and Television Review and Classification Board', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:37:02', '2021-01-20 16:37:02'),
(947, 18, 1, 'It enforces banking laws and regulates the banking industry.', 'Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:37:28', '2021-01-20 16:37:28'),
(948, 21, 1, 'The nurse is preparing to give a brevity flow tube feeding using a large syringe. Prior to infusion, the nurse should:', 'Verifying tube placement and residual is a standard of care for a tube feeding.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:37:38', '2021-01-20 16:37:38'),
(949, 18, 1, 'Refers to a court which is created by law to amicably settle disputes between neighbors within a particular community', 'Barangay court', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:37:55', '2021-01-20 16:37:55'),
(950, 21, 1, 'The nurse explains that the newest endoscopic procedure for examining the small intestine is the:', 'The capsule camera is swallowed and transmits information about the small bowel to a receiver on a belt around the patient’s waist.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:38:20', '2021-01-20 16:38:20'),
(951, 21, 1, 'After receiving a tube feeding, the patient becomes sweaty and has abdominal distention with diarrhea. The nurse assesses that this is because of:', 'Dumping syndrome is caused by infusing a tube feeding too fast or infusing a tube feeding that is too rich a formula.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:38:55', '2021-01-20 16:38:55'),
(952, 18, 1, 'Refers to that sector of society composed of NGO’s, cause oriented groups and advocacy groups that promotes the welfare of the people against all forms of abuse and exploitation.', 'Civil society', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:39:17', '2021-01-20 16:39:17'),
(953, 21, 1, 'The nurse assesses a risk factor that increases the chances of developing oral cancer, which is:', 'Alcohol is statistically proven to be a factor because of irritation of the oral mucosa.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:39:39', '2021-01-20 16:39:39'),
(954, 18, 1, 'Directly under the supervision of the Department of Justice, its most important function in the Criminal Justice System is to maintain and recognize the rule of law through the speedy delivery of services particularly in the prosecution and investigation of all crimes.', 'National Prosecution Service', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:39:42', '2021-01-20 16:39:42'),
(955, 21, 1, 'The nurse caring for a postoperative patient who has had lesions removed from his mouth has just returned to the unit. The initial care will focus on:', 'Suctioning must be done to ensure a patent airway. All other options should be addressed, but not as an initial implementation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:40:13', '2021-01-20 16:40:13'),
(956, 18, 1, 'Refers to all disciplines involved in the study of crimes and criminals.', 'Criminological enterprise', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:40:22', '2021-01-20 16:40:22'),
(957, 21, 1, 'The home health nurse observes the patient with esophageal cancer tilt his head back while eating, which could result in:', 'Tilting the head back not only makes it more difficult to eat but increases the risk of aspiration.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:40:51', '2021-01-20 16:40:51'),
(958, 18, 1, 'Refers to restraining or isolating criminals behind prison facilities to effectively protect society.', 'Crime control', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:40:55', '2021-01-20 16:40:55'),
(959, 21, 1, 'The nurse caring for a patient with esophageal surgery who has had stents placed in the esophagus instructs the patient how best to avoid regurgitation. The instruction should include:', 'Eating small meals will help with reflux. Keeping the head of the bed raised and not taking in excessive fluid with meals should be practiced.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:42:18', '2021-01-20 16:42:18'),
(960, 18, 1, 'The political will of the state to punish criminals in accordance with law.', 'Crime deterrence', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:42:37', '2021-01-20 16:42:37'),
(961, 21, 1, 'After administering promethazine (Phenergan) for nausea, the nurse takes extra precautionary implementations because of the common side effect of antiemetics, which is:', 'Most antiemetics cause drowsiness because of effects on the central nervous system, resulting in dizziness and confusion.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:42:57', '2021-01-20 16:42:57'),
(962, 18, 1, 'Refers to all governmental and non-governmental activities to thwart, preempt and stop the crime from occurring.', 'Crime prevention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:43:24', '2021-01-20 16:43:24'),
(963, 21, 1, 'The patient with a hiatal hernia should have a teaching plan to help with the reduction of the complaints of heartburn, regurgitation, and eructation. This would include instruction about:', 'Eating just prior to bedtime encourages reflux into the hernia and possible aspiration.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:43:36', '2021-01-20 16:43:36'),
(964, 18, 1, 'In the attempt to prevent crimes, what must be eliminated by the police?', 'Opportunity to commit crimes', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:43:55', '2021-01-20 16:43:55'),
(965, 18, 1, 'Primary objective of law enforcement.', 'Crime prevention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:44:28', '2021-01-20 16:44:28'),
(966, 21, 1, 'Your patient is to receive cimetidine IV, 300 mg, diluted in 20 mL of 0.9% normal saline solution. This is to be administered over 30 minutes. The delivery system is 15 gtt/mL. The IV controlling machine should be set for how many mL/hour?', 'Set the machine for 600 mL/hour. To give 300 mL in 30 minutes requires that the machine be set for 600 mL/hour.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:44:52', '2021-01-20 16:44:52');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `lesson_id`, `enabled`, `question_text`, `justification`, `difficulty`, `time`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(967, 18, 1, 'An attached agency of the office of the president tasked to implement and undertake drug law enforcement.', 'PDEA', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:44:57', '2021-01-20 16:44:57'),
(968, 21, 1, 'The 60-year-old patient who has just been diagnosed with cancer of the stomach says, “I feel blank and numb.” The nurse’s best response would be:', 'Patients who may seem overwhelmed need to talk and express their feelings, even if they are not sure of what they are.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:45:27', '2021-01-20 16:45:27'),
(969, 18, 1, 'In making arrests under rule 113, Sec 5, par 3(fugitives from justice) of the rules of court, what is the duty of the arresting officer?', 'Either a and b', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:46:04', '2021-01-20 16:46:04'),
(970, 21, 1, 'On assessment at an intake examination, the nurse notes a characteristic of an inguinal hernia that should be reported immediately, which is:', 'A hernia that cannot be reduced is at risk for strangulation and should be addressed immediately.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:46:17', '2021-01-20 16:46:17'),
(971, 18, 1, 'When an offense has in fact been committed, and he has personal knowledge of facts indicating that the person  to be arrested has committed it; this contemplates warantless arrest involving:', 'Both a and b', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:46:38', '2021-01-20 16:46:38'),
(972, 21, 1, 'The goal for your patient with gastritis who has experienced nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea is to have a return of normal elimination patterns. Which of the following best reflects this goal in a measurable manner?', 'Goals are to be specific and measurable. The patient knows his normal pattern.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:46:51', '2021-01-20 16:46:51'),
(973, 18, 1, 'Refers to all the systems and interplay of activities in the community which addresses all the negative factors affecting security, health and welfare of the public in natural calamities, disaster, famine, criminality, drought and epidemics.', 'Social defense', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:48:02', '2021-01-20 16:48:02'),
(974, 21, 1, 'The nurse is caring for a patient hemorrhaging from a peptic ulcer when the patient complains of sharp sudden pain, with a rapidly deteriorating condition. Initially, the nurse should:', 'With a rapidly deteriorating patient, the nurse should collect all the information that will need to be reported.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:48:03', '2021-01-20 16:48:03'),
(975, 21, 1, 'The nurse has collected several stool specimens that are to go to the laboratory. The nurse should:', 'Parasite and ova specimens should be taken to the laboratory immediately while the parasites are still alive. Specimens for evaluation of pathogenic organisms should be kept cool.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:48:36', '2021-01-20 16:48:36'),
(976, 18, 1, 'A blueprint for a responsive and well suited anti crime machinery that shall operate its strategic purposes.', 'National Anti Crime Strategy', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:48:41', '2021-01-20 16:48:41'),
(977, 21, 1, 'Your 34-year-old patient is admitted with severe diarrhea and fatigue, which has been going on for several days. Why might continued diarrhea cause chronic fatigue?', 'Rapid transition of foods through the GI tract prevents absorption of nutrients.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:49:08', '2021-01-20 16:49:08'),
(978, 18, 1, 'Period prescribed by law for the preliminary investigation to be undertaken by the prosecutor.', '10 days', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:49:17', '2021-01-20 16:49:17'),
(979, 21, 1, 'The patient inquires if the new type of gastric analysis is going to require multiple withdrawals of gastric content for evaluation of the presence of hydrochloric acid throughout the day. The nurse replies:', 'Dye is given orally and, if there is hydrochloric acid, the dye will be excreted in the urine in about 2 hours.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:49:40', '2021-01-20 16:49:40'),
(980, 18, 1, 'It is defined as “… The machinery of the state or government which enforces the rules of conduct necessary to protect life and property and maintain peace and order”.', 'Criminal justice system', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:49:51', '2021-01-20 16:49:51'),
(981, 21, 1, 'Stool softeners are prescribed to promote normal elimination of feces. The most appropriate way to ensure effectiveness of this type of drug is:', 'Adequate fluids must be maintained so the liquid is available; otherwise, the fecal mass will remain hard.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:50:17', '2021-01-20 16:50:17'),
(982, 21, 1, 'The set of findings that best indicate that the patient with intestinal obstruction has achieved normal hydration is:', 'These are all indications of fluid balance', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:51:21', '2021-01-20 16:51:21'),
(983, 18, 1, 'Its most important function in the Criminal Justice System is to maintain and recognize the rule of law through the speedy delivery of services particularly in the prosecution and investigation of all crimes.', 'Prosecution', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:51:58', '2021-01-20 16:51:58'),
(984, 21, 1, 'The nurse caring for a patient with a 3-day postoperative bowel resection observes that the suction apparatus is not working and the patient is becoming distended. The initial implementation should be to:', 'The simplest Implementation is always best to do initially. Change the patient’s position. Any tube adjustment is done later and with very small amounts. Irrigation may also be done later, but with 30 to 40 mL of saline.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:52:12', '2021-01-20 16:52:12'),
(985, 18, 1, 'They are referred to as the initiator of the criminal justice system.', 'Police', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:52:39', '2021-01-20 16:52:39'),
(986, 21, 1, 'Following abdominal surgery, your patient must cough and take deep breaths. How can you best achieve this with your patient?', 'Splinting decreases pain by supporting the muscles, thereby allowing better lung expansion.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:52:45', '2021-01-20 16:52:45'),
(987, 18, 1, 'Primary function of every court system', 'Help keep domestic peace', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:53:08', '2021-01-20 16:53:08'),
(988, 21, 1, 'The nurse describes a patient as “morbidly obese” because, with a weight of 387 pounds and a height of 2 meters, the patient’s body mass index (BMI) is:', 'Body mass index is calculated by dividing the weight in kilograms by the height in meters. Anyone weighing more than 30 kg is considered obese. 387 pounds/2.2 pounds/kg = 175 kg. 175 kg/2 meters = BMI of 87.5.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:53:37', '2021-01-20 16:53:37'),
(989, 18, 1, 'Tasked for the treatment  of national prisoners, which is under the Department of Justice.', 'Bureau of Corrections', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:53:38', '2021-01-20 16:53:38'),
(990, 18, 1, 'A special court tasked to handle criminal cases involving graft in corruption and other offenses committed by public officers and employees in connection with the performance of their functions.', 'SandiganBayan', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:54:06', '2021-01-20 16:54:06'),
(991, 21, 1, 'The cause of inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) is unknown. One factor being considered is an autoimmune reaction. A medication commonly used to treat IBD according to this theory is:', 'Steroids decrease the autoimmune response and lessen the inflammation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:54:08', '2021-01-20 16:54:08'),
(992, 21, 1, 'The nurse identifies a risk factor in an older man that puts him at risk for developing diverticulosis, which is:', 'A low-fiber diet increases the risk for diverticulitis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:54:38', '2021-01-20 16:54:38'),
(993, 18, 1, 'Highest court of the land with 1 chief justice and fourteen associate justices who may sit en banc or in division of 3, 5 and 7 members.', 'Supreme court', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:54:44', '2021-01-20 16:54:44'),
(994, 18, 1, 'Persons authorized by law to issue warrants of arrests.', 'Judges', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:55:09', '2021-01-20 16:55:09'),
(995, 21, 1, 'Patient teaching to promote self-care for the patient with diverticulosis should include avoidance of:', 'Foods containing seeds or small hard particles could become lodged in small pouches.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:55:10', '2021-01-20 16:55:10'),
(996, 18, 1, 'Most vital component of the criminal justice system due to its massive membership.', 'Community', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:56:13', '2021-01-20 16:56:13'),
(997, 18, 1, 'Passive instruments which decide controversies brought before them.', 'Courts', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:56:44', '2021-01-20 16:56:44'),
(998, 18, 1, 'Considered as the second pillar of the Philippine criminal justice system, The National Prosecution Service is under the;', 'Department of Justice', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:57:13', '2021-01-20 16:57:13'),
(999, 18, 1, 'The course of action or process whereby accusations are brought before the court of justice to determine the guilt of the accused.', 'Prosecution', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:57:43', '2021-01-20 16:57:43'),
(1000, 18, 1, '. Under this law, the uniform system of preliminary investigation was established giving the complainant and respondent in a preliminary investigation the right to confront each other and their witnesses.', 'RA 5189', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:58:15', '2021-01-20 16:58:15'),
(1001, 18, 1, 'Complaints must be supported by a _______.', 'Verified affidavit', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:58:53', '2021-01-20 16:58:53'),
(1002, 18, 1, 'The investigating fiscal must resolve the case within ___ days from its termination giving the parties copies of his resolution.', '10', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:59:32', '2021-01-20 16:59:32'),
(1003, 18, 1, 'Submitted by the accused to answer the complaint against him.', 'Counter affidavit', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 16:59:58', '2021-01-20 16:59:58'),
(1004, 21, 1, 'The nurse includes in the teaching plan information about when and where specific digestion of food takes place (select all that apply):\r\n1. Renin breaks down milk protein in the stomach. \r\n2. Lipase breaks down fats in the stomach. \r\n3. Pepsin begins breakdown of proteins in the stomach. \r\n4. Liver and pancreatic secretions break down fats in the small bowel. \r\n5. Ptyalin (amylase) breaks down carbohydrates in the mouth.', 'All options are correct for process and location.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:00:19', '2021-01-20 17:00:19'),
(1005, 18, 1, 'The court of last resort, all the justices are appointed by the president from a list submitted by the ______ to fill up any vacancy within 90 days.', 'Judicial and Bar Council', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:00:28', '2021-01-20 17:00:28'),
(1006, 18, 1, 'Retirement age for a justice of the Supreme Court is ____.', '70 years old', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:01:08', '2021-01-20 17:01:08'),
(1007, 21, 1, 'The home health nurse suggests dietary changes to an older woman to help prevent constipation, which include (select all that apply):\r\n1. addition of whole-grain cereal.\r\n2. cessation of laxative use.\r\n3. increase in liquid intake.\r\n4. decrease in sugar intake.\r\n5. eating fresh vegetables.', 'All options not only improve nutrition, but reduce the risk of constipation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:01:38', '2021-01-20 17:01:38'),
(1008, 18, 1, 'Established under the Judiciary Reorganization Act of 1980, BP 129 it is composed of one presiding justice and 68 associate justices all of whom are appointed by the president, and operates in 10 divisions each comprising of five members.', 'Court of Appeals', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:01:38', '2021-01-20 17:01:38'),
(1009, 18, 1, 'Created by law to hear cases involving civil aspects of our Muslim brothers.', 'Shari’a Courts', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:03:02', '2021-01-20 17:03:02'),
(1010, 21, 1, 'The nurse caring for a patient with achalasia can help the patient reduce swallowing difficulty by (select all that apply):\r\n1. identify foods that cause a problem.\r\n2. experiment with different eating positions.\r\n3. elevate the head of the bed at night.\r\n4. suggest eating more rapidly.\r\n5. offer small bites of fresh vegetables.', 'Eating rapidly and eating small bites increase swallowing difficulties.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:03:14', '2021-01-20 17:03:14'),
(1011, 18, 1, 'Under the legal system in the Philippines as provided by Article VIII Section 15 of the 1987 Constitution, the Supreme Court must decide or resolve a case or matter within the period from date of submission;', '24 months', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:03:33', '2021-01-20 17:03:33'),
(1012, 18, 1, 'Under the legal system in the Philippines as provided by Article VIII Section 15 of the 1987 Constitution, the Court of Appeals must decide or resolve a case or matter within the period from date of submission;', '12 months', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:04:04', '2021-01-20 17:04:04'),
(1013, 21, 1, 'The 92-year-old patient dehydrated from diarrhea exhibits anorexia and has lost 1 pound since yesterday. To help stimulate intake, the nurse would (select all that apply):\r\n1. moisten patient’s mouth with mouthwash.\r\n2. put away bedpans, urinals, and so forth.\r\n3. socialize with the patient during mealtime.\r\n4. check the fit of dentures.\r\n5. offer favorite foods.', 'All options are effective.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:04:23', '2021-01-20 17:04:23'),
(1014, 18, 1, 'Under the legal system in the Philippines as provided by Article VIII Section 15 of the 1987 Constitution, the Regional Trial Courts must decide or resolve a case or matter within the period from date of submission;', '3 months', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:04:40', '2021-01-20 17:04:40'),
(1015, 18, 1, 'For summary procedure in criminal cases, judgment is rendered within ___ days after termination of trial.\r\nUnder the legal system in the Philippines as provided by Article VIII Section 15 of the 1987 Constitution, the Supreme Court must decide or resolve a case or matter within the period from date of submission;', '1', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:05:13', '2021-01-20 17:05:13'),
(1016, 18, 1, 'Composed of 10 to 20 members this body is constituted every three years to oversee katarungang pambarangay.', 'Lupong Tagapamayapa', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:05:45', '2021-01-20 17:05:45'),
(1017, 18, 1, 'Consists of three members chosen by the opposing parties involved in a dispute at the barangay level.', 'Pangkat ng  Tagapagkasundo', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:06:24', '2021-01-20 17:06:24'),
(1018, 18, 1, 'As a general rule, if the penalty is less than 1 year imprisonment and the opposing parties are neighbors, co workers, the complainant must file the action before;', 'Lupong Tagapamayapa', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:07:04', '2021-01-20 17:07:04'),
(1019, 18, 1, 'Law which created the Katarungang Pambarangay.', 'RA 7160', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:07:43', '2021-01-20 17:07:43'),
(1020, 18, 1, 'Means the settlement of a dispute by a person or persons chosen to hear both sides and come to a decision.', 'Arbitration', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:08:09', '2021-01-20 17:08:09'),
(1021, 18, 1, 'RA 6981. Otherwise known as the “ _______________” to encourage , protect and give support to persons who may have witnessed a crime to participate in the legal system by giving their testimonies in court for the proper prosecution of cases in order to secure justice to those aggrieved by the commission of crimes.', 'Witness Protection Security and Benefit Act', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:08:43', '2021-01-20 17:08:43'),
(1022, 22, 1, 'When the nurse reads in the patient’s history that the patient has experienced otalgia, the nurse knows that the patient has:', 'Otic- is the root for ear, and -algia is the root term for pain of any type.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:15:44', '2021-01-20 17:15:44'),
(1023, 22, 1, 'The nurse assisting with a caloric test notes the specific patient response that indicates that the hearing disorder is a problem in the labyrinth, which is:', 'The appearance of nystagmus when warm or cold water is introduced into the ear is a positive indication that the hearing problem has its cause in the labyrinth.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:16:17', '2021-01-20 17:16:17'),
(1024, 22, 1, 'The 75-year-old patient has age-related changes in his ear. These changes include all but:', 'Otitis externa is an outer ear infection. This question requires knowledge of normal age-related changes in the ears.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:16:45', '2021-01-20 17:16:45'),
(1025, 22, 1, 'When doing the initial assessment on a patient with a hearing deficit, the patient reports that he often feels off balance and that he is dizzy when he stands up. These symptoms could be explained by:', 'Sinus infections can be an acute cause of hearing problems.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:17:14', '2021-01-20 17:17:14'),
(1026, 22, 1, 'A patient reports to the outpatient clinic, saying that he cannot hear well any more and was treated recently with gentamicin. The nurse suspects ototoxicity and inquires about:', 'Signs of ototoxicity are tinnitus, hearing loss, dizziness, and ataxia. Gentamicin is an antibiotic with potential for ototoxicity.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:17:39', '2021-01-20 17:17:39'),
(1027, 22, 1, 'The 75-year-old patient complains to the nurse that although she has cleaned her ears with cotton-tipped applicators for weeks, she still can’t hear her TV unless it is turned up loud, and she misses a great deal of conversations. On examination of the ears, the nurse anticipates that there will be:', 'Obstruction of the external canal with cerumen will result in a hearing loss. Cleaning ears with something like an applicator will pack the cerumen in the canal.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:18:16', '2021-01-20 17:18:16'),
(1028, 22, 1, 'The clinic patient tells you that her hearing loss has become more severe over the last 3 months. The clinic nurse makes arrangements for an evaluation for a hearing aid by an:', 'Audiologists assess patients for hearing aids. The other specialties are for ENT diseases.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:18:51', '2021-01-20 17:18:51'),
(1029, 22, 1, 'When a patient has a suspected vestibular disorder, the physician orders electronystagmography. The nursing instruction for this test will include:', 'Electronystagmography is used to detect vestibular lesions and requires a 3-hour period of NPO before the test. Coffee and tea should be avoided prior to the test.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:19:28', '2021-01-20 17:19:28'),
(1030, 22, 1, 'The nurse assessing the results of a Rinne test sees BC >AC. The nurse translates this to mean that the patient has:', 'When the bone conduction is greater than the air conduction (BC > AC), the patient has a conductive hearing loss. The normal finding for the Rinne test is that air conduction is greater than bone conduction (AC > BC).', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:20:00', '2021-01-20 17:20:00'),
(1031, 22, 1, 'The patient undergoing a Weber test says that the sound is louder in her left ear. This means that:', 'With Weber’s test, a conductive hearing loss is determined by the sound being heard loudest in the affected ear.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:20:32', '2021-01-20 17:20:32'),
(1032, 22, 1, 'When doing patient teaching for a patient who will be self-administering ear drops for an ear infection, the nurse would instruct the patient to:', 'The head is kept in the position to ensure that the drops penetrate deep into the external ear.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:21:15', '2021-01-20 17:21:15'),
(1033, 22, 1, 'When irrigating a patient’s ear, the nurse will:', 'The irrigation is done with warm water using a small-tipped syringe. The flow is directed upward. If the cerumen does not wash out, the procedure can be repeated, but with the same temperature water.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:21:50', '2021-01-20 17:21:50'),
(1034, 24, 1, 'It consists of the conditions and factors that surrounds and influences an individual that can cause certain behavior patterns.', 'All of the above', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:22:51', '2021-01-20 17:22:51'),
(1035, 22, 1, 'The nurse giving you a report on a newly admitted profoundly deaf patient says that the patient is confused and difficult to assess because she does not respond to questions appropriately or sometimes does not respond at all. The oncoming nurse will consider:', 'Profoundly deaf persons can be mistakenly assessed as being confused or disoriented when not wearing their hearing aids.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:22:53', '2021-01-20 17:22:53'),
(1036, 24, 1, 'It is also called as operant behavior which involves cognitive adaptation that enhances the human being’s ability to cope with changes in the environment and to manipulate the environment.', 'Learned', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:23:24', '2021-01-20 17:23:24'),
(1037, 22, 1, 'Choose the nursing diagnosis that would be most appropriate for a patient having ear surgery:', 'Patients who have had ear surgery are at risk for vertigo, fluid accumulation, or pressure in the operative ear. Because of the surgery and potential postoperative conditions, the patient may be at risk for a fall.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:23:24', '2021-01-20 17:23:24'),
(1038, 24, 1, 'It is the expert handling of a situation to reduce or eliminate danger or destruction.', 'Crisis Management', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:23:55', '2021-01-20 17:23:55'),
(1039, 22, 1, 'A significant instruction to a patient being discharged after ear surgery is to:', 'The patient should avoid blowing the nose to prevent backpressure in the eustachian tube. He or she should take stool softeners, limit activity until balance returns, and delay shampooing.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:24:12', '2021-01-20 17:24:12'),
(1040, 24, 1, 'It is a situation that set of circumstances wherein a suspected law violator is holding a person in captive by the use of force or threat of violence.', 'Hostage taking', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:24:26', '2021-01-20 17:24:26'),
(1041, 22, 1, 'A diabetic patient says that he can’t hear well anymore. Everything sounds garbled and distant. When he asks if a there is a hearing aid to improve his hearing, the nurse responds that a hearing aid may not help him because he has a:', 'The long-term diabetic has a sensorineural hearing loss that is not helped by hearing aids.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:24:41', '2021-01-20 17:24:41'),
(1042, 24, 1, 'What is the most important element of hostage negotiation?', 'Time', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:25:15', '2021-01-20 17:25:15'),
(1043, 22, 1, 'For the nursing care plan for a patient with Ménière’s disease, the nursing diagnosis that would take priority would be:', 'The nursing diagnosis that should take priority is that of preventing injury to the patient. The Ménière patient, because of dizziness, is prone to falls.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:25:20', '2021-01-20 17:25:20'),
(1044, 22, 1, 'In planning care for a child who has been diagnosed with a hearing impairment, and considering the impact of a hearing deficit, the nursing diagnosis that would be appropriate would be:', 'The loss of hearing and the mild stigma associated with hearing impairment puts the newly diagnosed child at risk for social isolation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:25:52', '2021-01-20 17:25:52'),
(1045, 24, 1, 'Crisis management has four (4) P’s. The first P stands for:', 'Predict', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:26:08', '2021-01-20 17:26:08'),
(1046, 22, 1, 'When teaching the patient with Ménière’s disease about managing the disease, the nurse will stress:', 'Use of alcohol and tobacco products affect the amount of fluid in the middle ear, making the symptoms of Ménière’s worse. The patient with Ménière’s disease should drink adequate fluid, use antiemetics as needed, and conserve energy during the day.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:26:32', '2021-01-20 17:26:32'),
(1047, 24, 1, 'The 2nd stage in the reactive phase of crisis management is:', 'Action Phase', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:26:48', '2021-01-20 17:26:48'),
(1048, 22, 1, 'The nurse points out to the client that of the activities in which he is regularly involved, the one that contributes to accumulation of cerumen in the external ear is:', 'Daily swimming in a chlorinated pool dries the cerumen. All the other options would reduce cerumen accumulation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:27:15', '2021-01-20 17:27:15'),
(1049, 24, 1, 'Which of the following do not belong to the category of personality disorder known as dramatic/erratic personality disorder?', 'Paranoid Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:27:43', '2021-01-20 17:27:43'),
(1050, 22, 1, 'A patient comes into the primary care clinic complaining of colds and ear pain with drainage. The nurse realizes that this patient may be experiencing:', 'Acute otitis media is connected with colds and drainage from the ear. A hearing loss may be experienced as well, but the pain and drainage put the need to intervene for the infection first.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:28:03', '2021-01-20 17:28:03'),
(1051, 22, 1, 'The young woman being admitted to the clinic service states that all the members of her family have been having a hard time hearing. She says her hearing loss became much more pronounced when she was pregnant. You suspect that this patient has a type of hearing loss called:', 'Otosclerosis is hereditary and develops in young women, worsening with pregnancy.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:28:32', '2021-01-20 17:28:32'),
(1052, 24, 1, 'It is a personality disorder characterized by a lack of interest in social relationships, a tendency towards a solitary lifestyle, secretiveness, and emotional coldness.', 'Schizoid Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:28:50', '2021-01-20 17:28:50'),
(1053, 22, 1, 'Patient teaching for a patient with Ménière’s disease includes which of the following?', 'A low-sodium diet and diuretics between attacks will prevent edema, which could cause an attack.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:29:10', '2021-01-20 17:29:10'),
(1054, 24, 1, 'Individuals who have low level of intelligence may commit crime because of their low knowledge. This explanation falls into what?', 'Personality Theory', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 17:29:21', '2021-01-20 17:29:21'),
(1055, 22, 1, 'When an older patient went to his nephew’s wedding, he had a hard time hearing people talk. He says that he has no difficulty hearing his wife when she talks to him at home but he seemed to have more problems at the wedding reception. The nurse responds:', 'This conductive hearing loss is one associated with normal aging.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:01:59', '2021-01-20 18:01:59'),
(1056, 22, 1, 'A patient has been taking 10 aspirin tablets a day for his arthritis. He comes into the clinic complaining of a ringing in his ears. The nurse, after assessing the patient, tells him:', 'Tinnitus in an indication of ASA toxicity. He should stop taking aspirin and contact his physician for a different prescription.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:03:23', '2021-01-20 18:03:23'),
(1057, 22, 1, 'Behaviors that would alert the nurse to a possible hearing deficit in the patient would be (select all that apply):\r\n1. watching the speaker’s mouth.\r\n2. giving inappropriate answers to questions.\r\n3. complaining about people muttering and mumbling.\r\n4. not responding when spoken to.\r\n5. turning the good ear to the speaker.', 'All options listed are cues about a hearing deficit.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:04:27', '2021-01-20 18:04:27'),
(1058, 22, 1, 'The nurse has noted some common characteristics in persons with conductive hearing loss, which are (select all that apply):\r\n1. hearing adequately in noisy settings.\r\n2. hearing sounds, but having difficulty understanding speech.\r\n3. hearing aids improve hearing.\r\n4. a history of diabetes mellitus.\r\n5. speaking in a normal volume.', 'Persons with conductive loss can hear in a noisy setting and have hearing improvement with hearing aids. Persons with conductive loss speak at a normal or soft volume as they can hear themselves. Muffled sounds and a history of diabetes would be associated with sensorineural hearing loss.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:05:39', '2021-01-20 18:05:39'),
(1059, 22, 1, 'The nurse uses a diagram to show the physiology of hearing. After sound has entered the external ear, the sound is then conducted through the (arrange the options in sequence):\r\n1. tympanic membrane.\r\n2. sensory receptors.\r\n3. oval window.\r\n4. acoustic nerve to the brain.\r\n5. malleus, incus, and stapes.', 'The sound impulse, after entering the external ear, goes to the tympanic membrane, through the malleus, incus and stapes, oval window, and sensory receptors in the inner ear, and then through the acoustic nerve to the brain.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:07:55', '2021-01-20 18:07:55'),
(1060, 25, 1, 'The 60-year-old patient who has had an enucleation asks when he can get his prosthesis fitted. The nurse responds that the prosthesis will be fitted by an optician in approximately:', 'After an enucleation, the patient is fitted with a prosthesis in 1 month', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:21:02', '2021-01-20 18:21:02'),
(1061, 25, 1, 'The patient who has been taking opioid medication for postoperative pain exhibits pinpoint pupils. The anatomic portion of the eye that has been affected by the medication is the:', 'The choroid of the eye contains the pupil and iris.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:22:18', '2021-01-20 18:22:18'),
(1062, 25, 1, 'The nurse explains that the portion of your eye that will make it possible for you to see in a darkened environment is the:', 'The eye uses rods to accommodate to dim light. Cones are the color receptors. The optic nerve transmits to the brain all sensory input from the eye.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:22:42', '2021-01-20 18:22:42'),
(1063, 25, 1, 'When being interviewed, a 50-year-old patient says that he cannot see the newspaper as well as he used to. You know that vision changes from near to far because:', 'Accommodation or adjustment of the lens by contraction and expansion of the ciliary muscle allows us to see far or near.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:23:19', '2021-01-20 18:23:19'),
(1064, 25, 1, 'During the initial assessment of a very thin patient at the eye clinic, the nurse notes that the patient has very prominent eyes. The nurse should inquire about a history of:', 'The appearance of the patient and the prominence of the eye (exophthalmos) would lead the nurse to inquire about a thyroid disorder, most likely Graves’ disease or hyperthyroidism.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:23:51', '2021-01-20 18:23:51'),
(1065, 25, 1, 'When you ask your patient about his vision, he says that the last time he had it tested, it was recorded as 20/50. This means that:', 'The Snellen eye chart is read at 20 feet. The last line the patient can read with no more than two errors is recorded. In this case, the patient was able to read the 50-foot line at 20 feet. This means that he is reading at 20 feet what a person with normal vision can read at 50 feet.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:24:25', '2021-01-20 18:24:25'),
(1066, 25, 1, 'The nurse recognizes that the patient who is being evaluated for a visual impairment does not have glaucoma because the tonometry reveals an intraocular pressure of:', 'The normal intraocular pressure is between 12 and 21 mm Hg. If the patient had glaucoma, the intraocular pressure would be abnormally high.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:25:01', '2021-01-20 18:25:01'),
(1067, 25, 1, 'The nurse explains to the patient who is to have a pneumotonometry study of the eye that this procedure requires that:', 'A pneumotonometer directs a puff of air at the surface of the eye, measuring intraocular pressure by measuring the resistance to the air. The eye is anesthetized prior to the evaluation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:25:36', '2021-01-20 18:25:36'),
(1068, 25, 1, 'The nurse performing the eye irrigation would:', 'The direction of the flow should be from the inner to the outer canthus.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:26:09', '2021-01-20 18:26:09'),
(1069, 25, 1, 'The nurse would include in the information given to a patient who is using topical eye medications to:', 'The eye drops should be dropped into the lower lid and the nurse should press the tear duct to slow absorption.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:26:39', '2021-01-20 18:26:39'),
(1070, 25, 1, 'When the patient asks what electroretinography is supposed to measure, the nurse responds that:', 'A contact lens is placed on the eye and retinal activity is assessed as lights are flashed into the eye. The other three options describe fluorescein angiography, visual evoked response, and opthodynamometry, respectively.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 18:56:06', '2021-01-20 18:56:06'),
(1071, 24, 1, 'A sudden and irresistible force compelling a person to do some action.', 'Compulsion', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:54:53', '2021-01-20 19:54:53'),
(1072, 25, 1, 'When doing patient education about protecting vision, you should tell the patient that:', 'Eye examinations every 2 years are recommended for persons over 40. All the other options are indications that the person should consult a physician for an eye disorder.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:55:12', '2021-01-20 19:55:12'),
(1073, 24, 1, 'False interpretation of an external stimulus refers to ___.', 'Hallucination', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:55:17', '2021-01-20 19:55:17'),
(1074, 24, 1, 'The most important element of hostage negotiation is:', 'Time', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:55:44', '2021-01-20 19:55:44'),
(1075, 25, 1, 'The nurse instructs a family member how to guide a visually impaired person when ambulating by:', 'Allowing the visually impaired person to walk slightly behind the helper and holding the helper’s arm is the most effective way to guide someone who is visually impaired.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:55:52', '2021-01-20 19:55:52'),
(1076, 24, 1, 'Crisis management has four (4) P’s. The first P stands for:', 'Predict', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:56:15', '2021-01-20 19:56:15'),
(1077, 24, 1, 'The 2nd stage in the reactive phase of crisis management is:', 'Action Phase', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:56:42', '2021-01-20 19:56:42'),
(1078, 24, 1, 'Which of the following do not belong to the category of personality disorder known as dramatic/erratic personality disorder?', 'Paranoid Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:57:19', '2021-01-20 19:57:19'),
(1079, 25, 1, 'The newly diagnosed patient with macular degeneration flings her book at the TV set and furiously says, “I can’t read this blasted book and I can’t see what is on the stupid TV!” The nurse recognizes this behavior as:', 'There is frequently a grieving process that accompanies the realization that there will be deteriorating vision and ultimate blindness.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:58:00', '2021-01-20 19:58:00'),
(1080, 24, 1, 'It is a personality disorder characterized by a lack of interest in social relationships, a tendency towards a solitary lifestyle, secretiveness, and emotional coldness.', 'Schizoid Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:58:26', '2021-01-20 19:58:26'),
(1081, 25, 1, 'The nurse explains that the correct term to use for a patient with a vision disorder is:', 'The term visual impairment is a medically accepted term to use for patients with a vision loss', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:58:48', '2021-01-20 19:58:48'),
(1082, 24, 1, 'Deceit and manipulation are considered essential features of this disorder. This disorder is known as:', 'Anti-Social Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:59:15', '2021-01-20 19:59:15'),
(1083, 25, 1, 'A nursing diagnosis for a visually impaired patient might include all of the following except:', 'Patients with a visual impairment are not at risk for delayed development. They will have a nursing diagnosis of Impaired sensory perception, Ineffective coping, and Self-care deficit.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:59:21', '2021-01-20 19:59:21'),
(1084, 25, 1, 'Implementations that are appropriate in the care plan for a visually impaired person include:', 'The nurse should announce her or his presence in the room and address the patient before touching him or her. The bed should be in the lowest position and the door should be open to avoid social isolation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 19:59:56', '2021-01-20 19:59:56'),
(1085, 24, 1, 'It is a personality disorder characterized by a pattern of excessive emotionality and attention-seeking, including an excessive need for approval and inappropriate seductiveness, usually beginning in early adulthood.', 'Histrionic Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:00:11', '2021-01-20 20:00:11'),
(1086, 25, 1, 'The patient with glaucoma who is using a beta-adrenergic blocking agent, timolol (Timoptic) should be monitored for:', 'Beta-adrenergic blocking agents cause bronchospasm and tachycardia.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:00:24', '2021-01-20 20:00:24'),
(1087, 24, 1, 'A disorder and its derivatives can be caused by excessive praise and criticism in childhood, particularly that from parental figures. It is frequently mistaken for self-centered.', 'Narcissistic Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:00:40', '2021-01-20 20:00:40'),
(1088, 25, 1, 'The patient tells you that he has to hold his paper farther and farther away from his face to read it. It has become a joke in his family about how far away he needs to hold reading material. You tell the patient:', 'Presbyopia is a normal age-related change. It is caused by changes in the ciliary muscles. Corrective lenses such as bifocals are used to correct this visual change.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:00:54', '2021-01-20 20:00:54'),
(1089, 24, 1, 'The characteristic of this personality disorder is that, it has difficulty making everyday decisions without an excessive amount of advice and reassurance from others and needs others to assume responsibility for most major areas of his or her life.', 'Dependent Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:01:15', '2021-01-20 20:01:15'),
(1090, 25, 1, 'The nurse explains that LASIK surgery and PRK are new methods to correct refractive errors surgically. These procedures are used to reshape the:', 'Both surgical procedures are used to reshape the cornea. The test taker will need to determine which structure of the eye will need surgery to correct vision.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:01:23', '2021-01-20 20:01:23'),
(1091, 24, 1, 'A person who is afraid of blood is suffering what phobia?', 'Hematophobia', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:01:46', '2021-01-20 20:01:46'),
(1092, 25, 1, 'The patient reports to the home health nurse that she is having cloudy vision and seeing spots and halos around lights. Based on these complaints, the nurse makes arrangement to have a medical evaluation for:', 'Cataracts are the cause of cloudy vision and seeing spots or halos.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:01:49', '2021-01-20 20:01:49'),
(1093, 25, 1, 'The nurse explains that the difference between open-angle and closed-angle glaucoma is that, with closed-angle glaucoma:', 'Closed-angle glaucoma has an acute onset with eye pain and other systemic symptoms, such as nausea and vomiting. It is an ocular emergency to get the intraocular pressure reduced.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:02:19', '2021-01-20 20:02:19'),
(1094, 24, 1, 'It is a personality disorder that is characterized by a general psychological inflexibility, rigid conformity to rules and procedures, perfectionism, moral code, and/or excessive orderliness.', 'Obsessive-Compulsive Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:02:23', '2021-01-20 20:02:23'),
(1095, 24, 1, 'The agency charge with the handling of crisis particularly man-made incidents is known as____.', 'NPOC', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:02:47', '2021-01-20 20:02:47'),
(1096, 25, 1, 'The nurse considers in planning care for a patient with glaucoma that this disorder is caused by:', 'Glaucoma is caused by an increase in intraocular pressure.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:02:48', '2021-01-20 20:02:48'),
(1097, 24, 1, 'The agency charge with the handling of crisis particularly natural incidents is known as____.', 'NDRRMC', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:03:19', '2021-01-20 20:03:19'),
(1098, 25, 1, 'A patient presents in the emergency room complaining of severe pain in his eye, and is seeing halos around lights and feeling nauseous. You suspect that he may be experiencing:', 'Sudden onset of acute eye pain with nausea and vomiting and halos around lights are all symptoms of angle-closure glaucoma. The acute pain is caused by sudden blockage of the fluid channels in the eye.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:03:21', '2021-01-20 20:03:21'),
(1099, 25, 1, 'The nurse explains to a patient with retinal detachment that the surgical implementation that is most effective is:', 'Scleral buckling is used to hold the retinal repair in place. The band is left in place to keep the layers of the eye tissue together.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:03:48', '2021-01-20 20:03:48'),
(1100, 24, 1, 'Ador is very shy and evades people. He is suffering:', 'Avoidant Personality Disorder', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:03:53', '2021-01-20 20:03:53'),
(1101, 24, 1, 'A person who is afraid of blood is suffering what phobia?', 'Hematophobia', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:04:25', '2021-01-20 20:04:25'),
(1102, 25, 1, 'The nurse assesses an 80-year-old for age-related changes to the eye, which are (select all that apply):\r\n1. decreased tear production.\r\n2. eyeball sunk deep in orbit.\r\n3. hyperopia.\r\n4. eye lashes diminished.\r\n5. arcus senilis.', 'Eyelash diminution is not a consistent finding in older adults. All the other options are common eye changes related to advancing age.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:05:04', '2021-01-20 20:05:04'),
(1103, 24, 1, 'It is known as the process of interpersonal communication in which interested parties resolve disputes, agree upon courses of action, bargain for individual or collective advantage, and/or attempt to craft outcomes which serve their mutual interests. It is usually regarded as a form of alternative dispute resolution.', 'Negotiation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:05:20', '2021-01-20 20:05:20'),
(1104, 25, 1, 'The nurse is aware that the refractive media of the eye is made up of the (select all that apply):\r\n1.	aqueous humor.\r\n2.	retina.\r\n3.	vitreous humor.\r\n4.	cornea.\r\n5.	lens.', 'The retina is not part of the refractive media. All the other options are components of the refractive media.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:05:56', '2021-01-20 20:05:56'),
(1105, 24, 1, 'In a hostage negotiation the captive or the hostage shall never say “NO” to the hostage-taker(s).', 'False', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:06:01', '2021-01-20 20:06:01'),
(1106, 24, 1, 'The term \"Stockholm Syndrome\" was coined by the criminologist and psychiatrist Nil Bejerot, who assisted the police during the robbery, and referred to the syndrome in a news broadcast. Who originally give the term Stockholm syndrome?', 'Frank Ochberg', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:06:36', '2021-01-20 20:06:36'),
(1107, 25, 1, 'The nurse assesses the patient’s accommodation by (select all that apply):\r\n1.	holding his or her finger approximately 20 inches in front of the patient’s eyes.\r\n2.	observing for pupillary constriction.\r\n3.	assessing for convergence.\r\n4.	noting blinking.\r\n5.	moving his or her finger slowly toward the patient’s nose.', 'Assessment for blinking is not part of the accommodation assessment. All the others are part of the accommodation assessment. The nurse holds his or her finger approximately 20 inches in front of the patient’s eyes, slowly moved the finger toward the patient’s nose, assessing for pupillary constriction and convergence.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:06:41', '2021-01-20 20:06:41'),
(1108, 24, 1, 'Under the concept of three (3) stage negotiation, negotiation must be performed through opening, bargaining, and ____.', 'Closing', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:07:05', '2021-01-20 20:07:05'),
(1109, 24, 1, 'It is a subjectively defined behavioral characteristic, assigned to those with rare or dysfunctional conditions.', 'Abnormal Behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:07:40', '2021-01-20 20:07:40'),
(1110, 25, 1, 'The patient who has had surgery this morning for cataracts is now going home. Discharge instructions include that the patient should (select all that apply):\r\n1.	sleep on the operated side.\r\n2.	use stool softeners.\r\n3.	avoid bending over.\r\n4.	not lift anything heavier than 5 pounds.\r\n5.	not wear an eye shield at night.', 'The postcataract surgery patient should sleep on the unoperated side with the eye shield in place, avoid heavy lifting, and use stool softeners to prevent straining.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:07:50', '2021-01-20 20:07:50'),
(1111, 24, 1, 'It is develop when one or more terrorists or criminals hold people against their will and try to hold off the authorities by force, threatening to kill the hostages if provoked or attacked.', 'Hostage Crisis', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:08:22', '2021-01-20 20:08:22'),
(1112, 24, 1, 'This is a type of hostage-taker which is viewed as a group of psychopaths with a cause, all under the leadership of one of the group. When caught in a criminal act, many of them rationalize their behavior by claiming to be revolutionaries who are merely seeking social justice. This hostage-taker is known as ___.', 'Psychotic Hostage-taker', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:08:57', '2021-01-20 20:08:57'),
(1113, 17, 1, 'When a patient complains of tachypnea, the nurse explains that the breathing pattern has altered because the (select all that apply):\r\n1.	increased pH levels stimulate chemoreceptors in the aorta and carotid, which stimulates the phrenic nerve\r\n2.	decreased O2 level signals the phrenic nerve to alter the respiration rate\r\n3.	muscles of respiration respond to the stimulus\r\n4.	brain has become hypoxic and causes an alteration in the respiration rate\r\n5.	deflated lung tissue results in an altered respiration rate', 'A decreased O2 level stimulates the phrenic nerve to signal the muscles of respiration to do the work of breathing. A decreasing pH level is the stimulus to the chemoreceptors. Neither the brain nor the lungs signal for tachypnea.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:09:27', '2021-01-20 20:09:27'),
(1114, 24, 1, 'What is the most important element of hostage negotiation?', 'Time', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:09:40', '2021-01-20 20:09:40'),
(1115, 24, 1, 'Under the Eight Stage Negotiation Process if the hostage negotiator tries to understand the hostage-taker and the negotiator also seek to hear and listen to the captor, what is the process practiced by the hostage negotiator?', 'Preparing and Opening', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:10:19', '2021-01-20 20:10:19'),
(1116, 17, 1, 'During the physical examination of a patient with respiratory difficulty, the nurse notices other clues to respiratory dysfunction, which are (select all that apply):\r\n1.	flushed facial skin\r\n2.	cyanotic nailbeds\r\n3.	protruding abdomen\r\n4.	curved spine\r\n5.	clubbed fingers', 'Clues to respiratory dysfunction are cyanotic nailbeds and clubbed fingers from inadequate oxygenation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:10:39', '2021-01-20 20:10:39'),
(1117, 24, 1, 'One policy in a hostage negotiation is to avoid mistake. If a hostage negotiator gives the hostage-taker no other alternative but to fight this mistake of negotiation is known as ___.', 'Cornering', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:10:50', '2021-01-20 20:10:50'),
(1118, 24, 1, 'Under the Special Procedure of the Philippine National Police Operational Procedure which of the following steps should not be undertaken during hostage situation?', 'Assault team shall target the hostage-taker immediately.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:11:36', '2021-01-20 20:11:36'),
(1119, 17, 1, 'Just prior to the scheduled spirometry test, the nurse instructs a patient to (select all that apply):\r\n1.	not smoke\r\n2.	use bronchodilator inhaler\r\n3.	exercise a few minutes\r\n4.	drink two glasses of fluid\r\n5.	avoid eating', 'Patients should not smoke, use bronchodilators, or exercise just prior to the test. Normal-sized meals and drinking fluid do not affect the test adversely.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:11:37', '2021-01-20 20:11:37'),
(1120, 17, 1, 'The nurse instructing a patient in deep breathing and coughing directs the patient to (place the options in the appropriate sequence):\r\n1.	place the hand on the abdomen to check rise and fall\r\n2.	inhale through the nose, pause 1 to 3 seconds, and then exhale\r\n3.	assume a high Fowler’s position\r\n4.	take 4 to 6 deep breaths\r\n5.	cough deeply', 'The exercise is done in a sequence to ensure open bronchioles and good deep cough.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:13:05', '2021-01-20 20:13:05'),
(1121, 24, 1, 'A woman with an unwanted pregnancy may be morally opposed by abortion. Specifically, what is this kind of conflict?', 'Avoidance-Avoidance Conflict', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:14:05', '2021-01-20 20:14:05'),
(1122, 24, 1, 'It is a kind of defense mechanism in which a person returns to an earlier stage of development in response to some perceived threat. An adult for instance who is unable to solve problems that confront him may resort to childish tactics. He may cry what he wants. This refers to:', 'Regression', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:14:50', '2021-01-20 20:14:50'),
(1123, 24, 1, 'It refers to the unpleasant feelings that resulted from the blocking of motive satisfaction- that is, the feelings we experience when something interferes with our wishes, hopes, plans and expectation. This is considered as a universal experience?', 'Frustration', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:15:17', '2021-01-20 20:15:17');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `lesson_id`, `enabled`, `question_text`, `justification`, `difficulty`, `time`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1124, 19, 1, 'The nurse explains that factors that affect stroke volume are (select all that apply):\r\n1.	contractility\r\n2.	climate\r\n3.	age\r\n4.	preload\r\n5.	afterload', 'Stroke volume is dependent on contractility, preload, and afterload. Age may affect all three, but the stroke volume, regardless of age, is dependent on these three factors.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:15:57', '2021-01-20 20:15:57'),
(1125, 24, 1, 'Emergency came from the Greek word “emergentia” meaning a dipping. Funk and Wagnall defined emergency as a sudden condition or state of affair calling for immediate action.', 'False', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:16:07', '2021-01-20 20:16:07'),
(1126, 24, 1, 'The word Crisis came from the Latin word “crisis”, which means separate. As defined by Funk and Wagnalls, crisis is turning points in the progress of an affair or a series of events.', 'No', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:16:41', '2021-01-20 20:16:41'),
(1127, 24, 1, 'Under the 4th P of crisis management, what is the phase of action the moment the On-Scene Command Post was established?', 'Action Phase', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:17:17', '2021-01-20 20:17:17'),
(1128, 19, 1, 'The nurse takes into consideration the age-related changes in the heart, which are (select all that apply):\r\n1.	Decrease in contractility\r\n2.	Thickened valves\r\n3.	Stiffened valves\r\n4.	Decreased SA node cells\r\n5.	Increased nerve fibers in ventricles', 'Aging thickens and stiffens the valves and reduces the cells in the SA node. Age decreases the nerve fibers in the ventricles.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:17:43', '2021-01-20 20:17:43'),
(1129, 24, 1, 'It is the population of behaviors exhibited by humans and influenced by culture, attitudes, emotions, values, ethics, authority, rapport, hypnosis, persuasion, coercion and/or genetics.', 'Human behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:17:55', '2021-01-20 20:17:55'),
(1130, 24, 1, 'It refers to the product of the mind.', 'Human behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:18:38', '2021-01-20 20:18:38'),
(1131, 19, 1, 'The nurse uses a picture to demonstrate the conduction pathway through the chambers of the heart. Arrange the following options in the correct sequence:\r\n1.	Atria contract\r\n2.	Conduction through bundle branches\r\n3.	AV node fires\r\n4.	Purkinje fibers conduct\r\n5.	SA node fires\r\n6.	Ventricles contract', 'The conduction pathway begins in the SA node, travels down the atrial wall, depolarizing the atria, to the AV node, bundle branches, and Purkinje fibers, contracting the ventricles.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:19:01', '2021-01-20 20:19:01'),
(1132, 24, 1, 'It is defined as deviating from the normal or average or differing from the typical (such as an aberration).', 'abnormal behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:19:08', '2021-01-20 20:19:08'),
(1133, 24, 1, 'Characteristically inadequate or distorted style of coping. Symptoms may resemble psychotic characteristics, but they are less dramatic and less amenable to treatment.', 'Personality Pattern Disturbance', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:19:46', '2021-01-20 20:19:46'),
(1134, 24, 1, 'Similar to personality pattern disturbance but the symptoms are somewhat more encapsulated and tend to resemble neurotic rather than psychotic styles (four subtypes).', 'Personality Trait Disturbance', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:20:16', '2021-01-20 20:20:16'),
(1135, 24, 1, 'Emotionally shallow but sometimes superficially engaging people who cannot conform to society’s demands. Symptoms vary from chronic lack of responsibility to extreme forms of acting-out.', 'Sociopathic Personality Disturbance', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:20:55', '2021-01-20 20:20:55'),
(1136, 20, 1, 'The nurse uses a picture to demonstrate the bullae and blebs associated with emphysema. The nurse points out that the difference between the two is that blebs (select all that apply):\r\n1.	are between the alveolar spaces in the lungs\r\n2.	are in the lung parenchyma\r\n3.	can rupture, causing the lungs to collapse\r\n4.	are responsible for diaphragm flattening\r\n5.	are precancerous', 'Blebs are growths inside the organ of the lung that enlarge and rupture, causing lung collapse. Bullae are the lesions between the alveolar spaces. Neither are the cause of diaphragm flattening nor are they precancerous.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:20:57', '2021-01-20 20:20:57'),
(1137, 24, 1, 'The word abnormal means \'away from the norm\'. Many population facts are measured such as height, weight and intelligence. Most of the people fall within the middle range of intelligence, but a few are abnormally stupid.', 'Deviation from Statistical Norms', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:21:36', '2021-01-20 20:21:36'),
(1138, 24, 1, 'Every culture has certain standards for acceptable behavior; behavior that deviates from that standard is considered to be abnormal behavior. But those standards can change with time and vary from one society to another.', 'Deviation from Social Norms', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:23:00', '2021-01-20 20:23:00'),
(1139, 24, 1, 'It is how the behavior affects the well-being of the individual and/or social group. Examples are a man who attempts suicide, an alcoholic who drinks so heavily that he or she cannot keep a job or a paranoid individual who tries to assassinate national leaders.', 'Maladaptive Behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:23:40', '2021-01-20 20:23:40'),
(1140, 24, 1, 'Disorganization of personality marked by impaired vocational and social functioning and intellectual deterioration.', 'Psychosis', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:24:07', '2021-01-20 20:24:07'),
(1141, 24, 1, 'Severe depression during the involution period without previous history of psychosis.', 'Involutional Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:24:58', '2021-01-20 20:24:58'),
(1142, 24, 1, 'Inappropriately exaggerated mood and marked change in activity level with associated thought disorder.', 'Affective Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:25:38', '2021-01-20 20:25:38'),
(1143, 24, 1, 'Cyclical disturbances involving various combination of or alternation between excitement and delusional optimism on the one hand and immobilizing, delusional depression on the other.', 'Manic-Depressive Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:26:26', '2021-01-20 20:26:26'),
(1144, 24, 1, 'Bizarre behavior; disturbances of thought and reality testing; emotional withdrawal; and varying levels of psychotic thinking and behavior.', 'Schizophrenic Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:50:55', '2021-01-20 20:50:55'),
(1145, 24, 1, 'Intellectual deterioration, social, and emotion apathy.', 'Simple Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:51:47', '2021-01-20 20:51:47'),
(1146, 24, 1, 'Extreme regression, mannerism, silliness.', 'Hebephrenic Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 20:52:26', '2021-01-20 20:52:26'),
(1147, 26, 1, 'The nurse assesses that the patient’s urine has become much more concentrated, which results from the effect of:', 'Aldosterone acts on the kidney tubules, affecting water retention and its attendant urine concentration.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:06:06', '2021-01-20 21:06:06'),
(1148, 26, 1, 'When the water absorption in the renal tubules becomes greater than normal, the nurse anticipates that the urine will become:', 'When more water is kept back in the body, the water left to form urine is less; therefore, the urine is more concentrated.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:07:21', '2021-01-20 21:07:21'),
(1149, 26, 1, 'The nurse explains that when oxygen is directed out of the arteries and into the capillaries, this process is:', 'Diffusion is the movement from areas of higher concentration to areas of lower concentration.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:08:19', '2021-01-20 21:08:19'),
(1150, 26, 1, 'The patient’s IV has been infusing at a very high rate and now the patient appears to be in fluid volume overload, as indicated by:', 'An IV infusing at a high rate is used to increase intravascular fluid volume, but there is an equalization level, after which the patient goes into fluid overload; this results in pulmonary edema.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:09:02', '2021-01-20 21:09:02'),
(1151, 24, 1, 'Extreme regression, bizarre motor behavior, such as posturing or stupor, periodic excitement and loss of control.', 'Catatonic Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:09:07', '2021-01-20 21:09:07'),
(1152, 26, 1, 'A small child is hospitalized with severe metabolic acidosis after ingesting a whole bottle of baby aspirin about 8 hours ago. The nursing care for this patient is geared toward reassuring the patient and', 'The baby aspirin was ingested too long ago to have vomiting or stomach aspiration be of any use. The child requires frequent assessment of neurological function because he or she may need mechanical ventilation.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:09:39', '2021-01-20 21:09:39'),
(1153, 24, 1, 'Unsystematized delusions, with or without hallucination. Extreme suspiciousness and hostility towards others.', 'Paranoid Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:09:48', '2021-01-20 21:09:48'),
(1154, 26, 1, 'The nurse explains that fluids carrying nutrients and wastes on a random basis throughout the body are carried primarily by:', 'The blood and lymph are the main media for transport of nutrients and wastes in the body.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:10:06', '2021-01-20 21:10:06'),
(1155, 24, 1, 'Delusional thinking that is more or less encapsulated and systematized. Personality organization and intellectual function less drastically affected than in schizophrenia.', 'none of these', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:10:16', '2021-01-20 21:10:16'),
(1156, 26, 1, 'The nurse clarifies that electrolytes, such as sodium and potassium, when dissolved, break down into smaller particles, which are called:', 'Electrolytes dissolved in water are ions.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:10:38', '2021-01-20 21:10:38'),
(1157, 24, 1, 'Impaired social, intellectual and/ or vocational functioning without disorganization of personality or loss of contact with reality. Impairment arises because of excessive defensiveness. Anxiety or disabling symptom that is usually symbolic efforts to resolve conflict.', 'Neurosis', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:10:41', '2021-01-20 21:10:41'),
(1158, 24, 1, 'Diffused fearfulness, tension, and restlessness w/h sometimes snowball into episodes of panic.', 'Anxiety Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:11:15', '2021-01-20 21:11:15'),
(1159, 26, 1, 'The nurse assists a dyspneic patient to sit in a high Fowler’s position. This aids gravity in helping the movement of oxygen from the pulmonary capillaries into the blood by the process of', 'Fowler’s position increases blood flow through the lungs and therefore facilitates better oxygen diffusion.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:11:21', '2021-01-20 21:11:21'),
(1160, 26, 1, 'The nurse evaluates the laboratory reports on electrolyte values carefully to assess the balance between positive and negative ions, which is regulated by the process of:', 'Diffusion allows the ions to support homeostatic balance.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:11:48', '2021-01-20 21:11:48'),
(1161, 24, 1, 'Repression or dissociation of certain aspect of experience or memory varying in intensity from sleepwalking to amnesias and multiple personality disturbance.', 'Dissociative Reactive', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:12:02', '2021-01-20 21:12:02'),
(1162, 26, 1, 'When the nurse hangs an IV bag with Na+, K+, and Cl, he is aware that ____ are being administered.', 'Sodium, potassium, and chlorides are electrolytes.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:12:15', '2021-01-20 21:12:15'),
(1163, 24, 1, 'Symbolic resolution of conflict that imitates the effects of physical illnesses like paralysis, blindness, anesthesia, etc.', 'Conversion Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:12:36', '2021-01-20 21:12:36'),
(1164, 26, 1, 'Each compartment of the body has a water-fluid distribution movement of its own. These fluids move and distribute themselves between these compartments via a process known as:', 'The intracellular and extracellular compartments contain water and dissolved substances. The water filters back and forth as needed to maintain homeostasis via osmolarity.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:12:42', '2021-01-20 21:12:42'),
(1165, 24, 1, 'Intense irrational fear of specific objects or events that may have a symbolic significance on the afflicted individual.', 'Phobic Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:13:00', '2021-01-20 21:13:00'),
(1166, 26, 1, 'The LPN is preparing to add a new IV of D5W with potassium to an existing line. The LPN notices that there is only 25 mL of urine collected over the last hour. The LPN’s best intervention is to:', 'The low urine output will allow K+ to build up to hazardous levels. K+ administration is dependent on adequate urine output. LPNs are required to report untoward findings to the RN.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:13:10', '2021-01-20 21:13:10'),
(1167, 24, 1, 'Repetitive, irrational thoughts (obsessions) and/or actions (compulsions) which usually involve some symbolic effort at conflict resolution.', 'Obsessive-Compulsive Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:13:32', '2021-01-20 21:13:32'),
(1168, 26, 1, 'Both the intracellular and extracellular fluids are made up of many different electrolytes, but the most abundant intracellular positively charged electrolyte is:', 'K+ is the most abundant electrolyte in the cell.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:13:43', '2021-01-20 21:13:43'),
(1169, 26, 1, 'The patient with metabolic acidosis should be closely monitored for the compensatory condition of:', 'When in metabolic acidosis, the body attempts to compensate by increasing respirations and creating respiratory alkalosis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:14:14', '2021-01-20 21:14:14'),
(1170, 24, 1, 'Depression, usually accompanied by guilt, feelings of inferiority, and anxiety.', 'Depressive Reaction', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:14:27', '2021-01-20 21:14:27'),
(1171, 26, 1, 'The K+ laboratory report shows a level of 5.2 mEq/L. The nurse will assess the patient closely for:', 'Arrhythmias can be triggered by hyperkalemia.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:14:45', '2021-01-20 21:14:45'),
(1172, 26, 1, 'A patient has renal damage because of diabetes, which puts the patient at risk for:', 'When the renal system cannot rid the body of enough potassium, this electrolyte builds up and a condition called hyperkalemia develops.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:15:11', '2021-01-20 21:15:11'),
(1173, 24, 1, 'Refers to antisocial acts that place the actor at risk of becoming a focus of the attention of criminal and juvenile justice professionals. Refers to acts that are injurious, prohibited under the law and that render the actor subject to intervention by justice professionals.', 'criminal behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:15:28', '2021-01-20 21:15:28'),
(1174, 26, 1, 'Hyperchloremia, as noted on a laboratory report, is usually associated with:', 'Chlorides bind with positively charged ions such as K+ in the patient with metabolic acidosis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:15:52', '2021-01-20 21:15:52'),
(1175, 24, 1, 'Refers to actions that are prohibited by the state and punish under the law.', 'criminal behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:15:59', '2021-01-20 21:15:59'),
(1176, 26, 1, 'Older adults are at risk for dehydration because of reduced thirst and aging kidneys. The nurse monitors for the early indicator of dehydration, which is:', 'Because older adults have poor skin turgor and urine concentration is difficult to assess, constipation is the earliest indicator of fluid deficit', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:16:26', '2021-01-20 21:16:26'),
(1177, 24, 1, 'Refers to actions that may be rewarding to the actor but that inflicts pain or one loss others. That is, Criminal behavior is anti social behavior.', 'criminal behavior', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:16:47', '2021-01-20 21:16:47'),
(1178, 26, 1, 'The nurse has two newly admitted patients with dehydration. One patient is dehydrated from heat exhaustion and the other from an overdose of Lasix. The finding that will present in both patients is:', 'Water has been lost; therefore, the red blood cells will concentrate and show artificially high hemoglobin and hematocrit values.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:17:02', '2021-01-20 21:17:02'),
(1179, 24, 1, 'This type is considered insane or psychotic. They often hear voices in their head telling them to commit the crime. They may also see visions.', 'Visionary Motive Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:17:23', '2021-01-20 21:17:23'),
(1180, 26, 1, 'The nurse clarifies that fluid balance is mainly monitored in the body by two systems, which are the:', 'The monitoring of basic fluid balance in the body is done by the renal and circulatory systems.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:17:36', '2021-01-20 21:17:36'),
(1181, 24, 1, 'This type displays no psychosis to the outside world, while on the inside the killer has a need to rid the outside world of what he considers immoral or unworthy. This type of killer will select a certain group of individuals to kill (prostitutes, young women, gay, men, etc.)', 'Mission Oriented Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:17:59', '2021-01-20 21:17:59'),
(1182, 26, 1, 'The nurse is aware that extracellular fluid osmolarity is primarily maintained by:', 'Sodium as the primary extracellular electrolyte controls the osmolarity of the extracellular fluid, either too much or too little.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:18:06', '2021-01-20 21:18:06'),
(1183, 24, 1, 'This type is in it for the fun. This killer gets a high from killing. He is very sadistic and kills for excitement.', 'Thrill Oriented Type', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:18:29', '2021-01-20 21:18:29'),
(1184, 26, 1, 'The nurse instructs that the healthy kidney adjusts the volume and composition of the filtrate that prevents excessive fluid loss by:', 'The kidney reabsorbs water and other electrolytes in response to chemical receptors.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 21:18:39', '2021-01-20 21:18:39'),
