(1276, 28, 1, 'These includes not only the sound physical development of the children, but also the cultivation of their intellectual perceptions and the nourishment of their appetitive and sensitive faculties:', 'Parental Authority', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:14:49', '2021-01-20 22:14:49'),
(1277, 29, 1, 'The patient who is stuporous, but reacts by withdrawing from painful stimuli, is said to be:', 'A stuporous patient who reacts to pain is semicomatose; no reaction to pain is comatose.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:15:11', '2021-01-20 22:15:11'),
(1278, 28, 1, 'Which of the following are socially incompetent, retarded intellectually from birth or early age, retarded at maturity and essentially incurable?', 'Mentally Retarded Children', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:15:12', '2021-01-20 22:15:12'),
(1279, 28, 1, 'What Republic Act lowers the age of majority to 18?', 'R.A. 6809', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:15:36', '2021-01-20 22:15:36'),
(1280, 29, 1, 'The nurse documents a normal finding from the Babinski reflex as a (the):', 'Normal cortical function causes the toes to curl downward. Abnormal findings would be the toes turning up and spreading.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:15:40', '2021-01-20 22:15:40'),
(1281, 28, 1, 'What Act is prohibiting the employment of children in public or private undertakings?', 'R.A. 7658', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:16:14', '2021-01-20 22:16:14'),
(1282, 29, 1, 'The nurse should assess the patient scheduled for an angiogram for:', 'Allergy to shrimp and other shellfish also indicates a probable allergy to the contrast medium.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:16:16', '2021-01-20 22:16:16'),
(1283, 28, 1, 'The surge biological maturation that results in reproductive capacity and relatively adult body size and contour is:', 'Puberty', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:16:42', '2021-01-20 22:16:42'),
(1284, 29, 1, 'A patient who has a pacemaker might be ineligible for:', 'Metal appliances may be affected by the magnetic field during an MRI.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:16:50', '2021-01-20 22:16:50'),
(1285, 28, 1, 'What kind of impediment will make the marriage void?', 'Relative Impediment', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:17:09', '2021-01-20 22:17:09'),
(1286, 29, 1, 'A patient with a severe head injury begins to assume a posture of flexed upper extremities, with plantar-flexed lower extremities. These assessments indicate:', 'Increasing pressure on the tissue above the midbrain results in abnormal flexion (decorticate posturing).', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:17:23', '2021-01-20 22:17:23'),
(1287, 28, 1, 'The following marriage shall be void from the very beginning under Art. 35 of the Family Code, except:', 'Those marriage solemnized by mayors publicly', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:17:41', '2021-01-20 22:17:41'),
(1288, 28, 1, 'Henna is nineteen years old but upon evaluation of a qualified psychiatrist, she is found to be incapable taking care of herself fully because of mental disability, therefore Henna is considered', 'Child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:18:02', '2021-01-20 22:18:02'),
(1289, 29, 1, 'The nurse caring for a 90-year-old patient with a closed head injury would immediately report:', 'The widening pulse pressure is an indicator of increased ICP. Respirations and temperature are returning to more normal levels. Older adults have a slowed pupillary response as they age.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:18:05', '2021-01-20 22:18:05'),
(1290, 28, 1, 'This type of abuser exercise poor judgment in their parenting decisions.', 'Accidental Abuser', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:18:31', '2021-01-20 22:18:31'),
(1291, 29, 1, 'A patient with generalized convulsive disorder has a nursing diagnosis of “Deficient knowledge related to lack of information about side effects of Dilantin.” Which goal and outcome criteria would be most appropriate?', 'Dilantin is irritating to GI tissues. Dilantin causes gingival hyperplasia, constipation, and drowsiness.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:18:57', '2021-01-20 22:18:57'),
(1292, 28, 1, 'Under Art 35 of the Family Code the following instances from which force sale or attachment of family home can be executed except:', 'For no debts incurred.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:19:14', '2021-01-20 22:19:14'),
(1293, 28, 1, 'Sonia does not have parents because her parents for good cause desires to be relieved of her care and custody, she is also dependent upon the public for support therefore Sonia is considered as:', 'Dependent Child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:19:38', '2021-01-20 22:19:38'),
(1294, 29, 1, 'The patient with meningitis who has a positive Brudzinski’s sign will:', 'Inflamed meninges will stimulate hip flexion to reduce meningeal discomfort.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:19:45', '2021-01-20 22:19:45');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `lesson_id`, `enabled`, `question_text`, `justification`, `difficulty`, `time`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1295, 28, 1, 'Manuel is not afflicted with insanity or mental defect, but he is unable to maintain normal social relations with others and the community in general due to emotional problems or complexes. Therefore Manuel is considered as:', 'Emotionally Disturb Child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:20:14', '2021-01-20 22:20:14'),
(1296, 29, 1, 'The assessment indicating that mannitol therapy for cerebral edema is effective in a patient with increased intracranial pressure (ICP) is:', 'Mannitol is a hyperosmolar diuretic that draws fluid from brain tissue into the bloodstream, which is then excreted by the kidneys. Decreasing pulse and widening pulse pressure indicate increased ICP.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:20:33', '2021-01-20 22:20:33'),
(1297, 28, 1, 'If a child is mentally retarded, physically handicapped, emotionally disturb and severe mentally-ill, the child is:', 'Disabled Child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:20:35', '2021-01-20 22:20:35'),
(1298, 28, 1, 'If a child is specially gifted, his parents shall report the fact to the:', 'National Center for Gifted Children', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:21:02', '2021-01-20 22:21:02'),
(1299, 29, 1, 'To prevent a postlumbar puncture headache, the patient is instructed to lie flat for at least:', 'Six hours is the optimum time in which the CSF fluid is regenerated to its prepuncture level.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:21:09', '2021-01-20 22:21:09'),
(1300, 28, 1, 'The classification of mentally retarded children who are severely or profoundly retarded, hence, the least capable group is:', 'Custodial Group', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:21:32', '2021-01-20 22:21:32'),
(1301, 29, 1, 'The nurse explains that the three symptoms characteristic of Cushing’s triad associated with increased ICP are:', 'Bradycardia, increasing blood pressure, and widening pulse pressure are all signs of increased ICP.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:21:53', '2021-01-20 22:21:53'),
(1302, 28, 1, 'The type of delinquents that generally commits the most serious infractions, is most often sent to correctional institution is:', 'Gang Delinquent', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:22:03', '2021-01-20 22:22:03'),
(1303, 29, 1, 'The nurse evaluates a positive outcome to the goal of teaching for the nursing diagnosis of: “Knowledge deficit related to conservation of energy in a patient with multiple sclerosis” when the patient says:', 'Balancing time between various activities indicates that the MS patient understands the need to conserve energy, not just to give up things or attempt to perform at a preillness level.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:22:23', '2021-01-20 22:22:23'),
(1304, 28, 1, 'The act of involving children whether male or female, who for money, profit or any other consideration or due to coercion or by influence of an adult, syndicate or group, to indulge in sexual intercourse or lascivious conduct is referred as:', 'Sexual Exploitation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:22:28', '2021-01-20 22:22:28'),
(1305, 28, 1, 'The involvement of a child in a sexual activity with an adult or any person older or bigger, in which for gratification of the older person’s needs or desires is:', 'Sexual Abuse', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:22:55', '2021-01-20 22:22:55'),
(1306, 29, 1, 'The patient in the ER states that she fell and hit her head and blacked out for a while, but became alert again. Suspecting an epidural hematoma, the nurse will be diligent in the assessment of:', 'Increasing blood pressure and a widening pulse pressure are indicators of increased ICP.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:22:57', '2021-01-20 22:22:57'),
(1307, 28, 1, 'An act allowing illegitimate children to use the surname of their father.', 'R.A. 9255', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:23:25', '2021-01-20 22:23:25'),
(1308, 29, 1, 'The intervention that should be added to the nursing care plan in supporting nutritional intake for a patient with Parkinson’s disease is to:', 'Thickened feedings are easier to swallow. Several small, protein-rich meals are preferable to large ones. A pureed diet is unappealing.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:23:25', '2021-01-20 22:23:25'),
(1309, 28, 1, 'Leo employed, permitted and allowed children below fifteen years of age to suffer to work in his private establishment where they are not directly under the responsibility of their parents or guardian, what act was committed by Leo?', 'Child Labor Exploitation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:23:50', '2021-01-20 22:23:50'),
(1310, 29, 1, 'A Parkinson’s patient is depressed because his drug protocol of L-dopa and Sinemet are no longer controlling his symptoms. The nurse’s response that would be the most helpful information is that:', 'The addition of other drugs to L-dopa may improve the conversion of L-dopa to dopamine. Palliative surgical implementations all have had little effect on controlling the symptoms.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:23:55', '2021-01-20 22:23:55'),
(1311, 28, 1, 'The following are classification of delinquency, except:', 'Non-utilitarian', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:24:19', '2021-01-20 22:24:19'),
(1312, 29, 1, 'A patient with Parkinson’s disease is considering taking St. John’s wort, an herbal remedy for depression, in addition to Sinemet and L-dopa. The best response is to make the patient aware that:', 'Herbal remedies interfere with effectiveness of prescribed parkinsonian drugs.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:24:30', '2021-01-20 22:24:30'),
(1313, 28, 1, 'What law establishes Family Courts granting them exclusive original jurisdiction over child and family cases?', 'R.A. 8369', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:24:41', '2021-01-20 22:24:41'),
(1314, 29, 1, 'The nursing assessment that would indicate a need for suctioning a patient with Guillain-Barré who is experiencing impaired breathing patterns because of neuromuscular failure is:', 'Increased pulse rate, adventitious breath sounds, and abdominal breathing indicate an impaired breathing pattern.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:25:00', '2021-01-20 22:25:00'),
(1315, 28, 1, 'The infliction of unreasonable punishment other than physical through excessive verbal assault or non-verbal harassment is:', 'Psychological Abuse', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:25:22', '2021-01-20 22:25:22'),
(1316, 29, 1, 'A family member asks the nurse what would be an appropriate gift for a patient with Parkinson’s disease. The most useful reply would be:', 'Satin sheets make moving in bed easier. Card games and jigsaw puzzles are frustrating due to the palsy. Hard-soled shoes provide better support than soft-soled shoes.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:25:28', '2021-01-20 22:25:28'),
(1317, 28, 1, 'Caesar unreasonably deprive Garry with his basic needs such as food, clothing, shelter, education general care, supervision by parents, Garry is suffering from:', 'Physical Neglect', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:25:44', '2021-01-20 22:25:44'),
(1318, 29, 1, 'When a patient falls to the floor in a generalized seizure, the nurse should:', 'Cradling the head and turning it to the side prevents injury and aspiration; restraint of limbs and insertion of an object into a patient’s mouth often result in injury.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:26:03', '2021-01-20 22:26:03'),
(1319, 28, 1, 'What term includes the guardian, and head of the institution or foster home, which has custody of a child?', 'Parents', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:26:06', '2021-01-20 22:26:06'),
(1320, 29, 1, 'In caring for the postcraniotomy patient, the nurse can help reduce ICP by:', 'Elevating the head of the bed at least 30 degrees helps with reducing ICP.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:26:34', '2021-01-20 22:26:34'),
(1321, 28, 1, 'Which of the following child abuse prevention refers to program aimed and eliminating the root causes of abuse and violence within our society?', 'Primary Prevention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:26:37', '2021-01-20 22:26:37'),
(1322, 28, 1, 'What family type home provide temporary shelter from 10 to 20 days for children who shall be during that period be under the observation and study for eventual placement by the Department of social Welfare?', 'Receiving Home', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:27:00', '2021-01-20 22:27:00'),
(1323, 29, 1, 'The nurse updates the nursing care plan for a patient with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis who is uniquely prone to depression because:', 'Because of their unimpaired intellect, ALS patients are able to assess their deterioration, which increases their risk for depression. Altered mobility, nutrition, and communication are common to many disorders.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:27:16', '2021-01-20 22:27:16'),
(1324, 28, 1, 'The parents of Melanie have deserted her for a period of six continuous months. Therefore Melanie is considered as:', 'Dependent Child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:27:26', '2021-01-20 22:27:26'),
(1325, 28, 1, 'The act, which results in non-accidental physical injury and/or unreasonable infliction of physical injury to the child, is:', 'Child Battering', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:27:48', '2021-01-20 22:27:48'),
(1326, 28, 1, 'The following are example of physical abuse, except:', 'Cursing a child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:28:11', '2021-01-20 22:28:11'),
(1327, 28, 1, 'Renato and Celia file legal separation in court but the court give the cooling period for the spouses filing for legal separation, how many months is the cooling period?', '6 months', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:28:40', '2021-01-20 22:28:40'),
(1328, 28, 1, 'Who shall be consulted in dealing with important family matters but should not interfere in the exercise of parental authority by parents to their children?', 'Grandparents', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:29:29', '2021-01-20 22:29:29'),
(1329, 28, 1, 'Which of the following includes not only the separation of parents but also irresponsible and quarreling parents?', 'Broken Home', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:29:49', '2021-01-20 22:29:49'),
(1330, 28, 1, 'The inadequate supervisions and discipline in the home have been commonly cited to explain delinquent behavior, this statement refers to:', 'Discipline in the Home', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:30:15', '2021-01-20 22:30:15'),
(1331, 28, 1, 'A parent who abuse a his child when he is confronted with a particular situation is considered as:', 'Situational Abuser', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:30:51', '2021-01-20 22:30:51'),
(1332, 28, 1, 'The conflicts between teachers and students or students versus students in school  refers to:', 'School Related Violence', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:31:28', '2021-01-20 22:31:28'),
(1333, 28, 1, 'What model were the father is the head of the family, the mother is the chief of the training table and head cheerleader?', 'Team model', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:31:54', '2021-01-20 22:31:54'),
(1334, 28, 1, 'One of the following reduces delinquency because it is something children do not want to lose.', 'Parental Love', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:32:17', '2021-01-20 22:32:17'),
(1335, 28, 1, 'The rule where the husband or wife cannot be examined for or against the other without consent, except in civil or criminal cases committed by one against the other, is:', 'Marriage Privilege Rule', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:32:41', '2021-01-20 22:32:41'),
(1336, 28, 1, 'Greg is a high school student who was able to accumulate twenty absences, what act was committed by Greg?', 'Truancy', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:33:10', '2021-01-20 22:33:10'),
(1337, 28, 1, 'In cases of disagreement of the parents, whose decision shall prevail?', 'Father', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:33:53', '2021-01-20 22:33:53'),
(1338, 28, 1, 'An act to help poor but deserving students to pursue their education by encouraging their employment during summer and/or Christmas vacation.', 'R.A. 7323', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:34:17', '2021-01-20 22:34:17'),
(1339, 28, 1, 'The institution or place of residence whose primary function is to give shelter and care to pregnant women and their infants before, during and after birth is:', 'Maternity Home', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:34:45', '2021-01-20 22:34:45'),
(1340, 28, 1, 'Which of the following Mentally retarded children has an I.Q. of 50 to 75?', 'Educable Group', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:36:07', '2021-01-20 22:36:07'),
(1341, 28, 1, 'Which of the following is not a cause of delinquency?', 'Loving Parents', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:37:01', '2021-01-20 22:37:01'),
(1342, 28, 1, 'The group of persons composing parents and children bond by marriage is considered as:', 'Family', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:37:24', '2021-01-20 22:37:24'),
(1343, 28, 1, 'Which of the following is not Characteristic of a gang?', 'Truancy', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:38:04', '2021-01-20 22:38:04'),
(1344, 28, 1, 'The term, which refers to any act by word or by deed, which debases, degrades or demeans the intrinsic worth and dignity of child as human being is:', 'Abuse', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:38:26', '2021-01-20 22:38:26'),
(1345, 28, 1, 'What law is known as the minor probation law?', 'P.D. 603', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:38:53', '2021-01-20 22:38:53'),
(1346, 28, 1, 'The Child abuse prevention that refers to steps/measures to keep a child safe from abuse and exploitation is:', 'Secondary Prevention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:39:48', '2021-01-20 22:39:48'),
(1347, 28, 1, 'Referring misguided minors to the agency of the government like boy’s town refers to:', 'Referral', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:40:08', '2021-01-20 22:40:08'),
(1348, 28, 1, 'Repeated body violence by one spouse against the other to such extent that the spouses can not continue living together without endangering the lives of both or either of them is a ground for:', 'Legal Separation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:40:32', '2021-01-20 22:40:32'),
(1349, 28, 1, 'Lito spank and slap his twelve years old son as a punishment for not following his illegal order, the act of Lito constitute as:', 'Child Abuse', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:40:59', '2021-01-20 22:40:59'),
(1350, 28, 1, 'Summer, a single woman gave birth to Rely. Summer cannot marry the father of Rely because he is a married man. Rely therefore is considered as:', 'Illegitimate Child', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:41:41', '2021-01-20 22:41:41'),
(1351, 28, 1, 'Lito a certified businessman and a bachelor at the age of 32 is qualified to adopt the a child,  what should be the age of the child that he can adopt?', '16', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:42:02', '2021-01-20 22:42:02'),
(1352, 28, 1, 'What is the child abuse prevention that refers to the actions to be taken in a situation where a child has already been abuse to prevent the recurrence of the same act?', 'Tertiary Prevention', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:43:20', '2021-01-20 22:43:20'),
(1353, 28, 1, 'The institution or person assuming the care, custody, cares and maintenance of children for placement in any child caring institution or home or custody of any persons for purposes of adoption, guardianship or foster care is', 'Child Placement Agency', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:43:46', '2021-01-20 22:43:46'),
(1354, 28, 1, 'The offices to coordinate with the council for welfare of children are the following offices, except:', 'Regional Trial Court', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:44:18', '2021-01-20 22:44:18'),
(1355, 28, 1, 'Any person duly appointed by the court or by competent authority to exercise care and custody or parental authority over the person employer is known as:', 'Parents', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:44:41', '2021-01-20 22:44:41'),
(1356, 28, 1, 'What theory argues that children learn deviant behavior socially, through exposure to others and by modeling of others behavior?', 'Social Control', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:45:05', '2021-01-20 22:45:05'),
(1357, 28, 1, 'Mario is a police officer who died on service, his legal spouse Nelia is about to claim the benefits that was left by Mario but somebody is also claiming that she is the spouse of Mario. The agency where they are claiming the benefits of the late police officer let the two claimants produce the best documentary evidence in marriage. What document is being asked by the agency?', 'Marriage Certificate', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:45:29', '2021-01-20 22:45:29'),
(1358, 29, 1, 'The nurse explains that neurotransmitters, which support smooth neural transmission, are (select all that apply):\r\n1.	acetylcholine\r\n2.	cerebrospinal fluid\r\n3.	dopamine\r\n4.	dendrite\r\n5.	epinephrine', 'Acetylcholine, dopamine, and epinephrine are neurotransmitters. CSF bathes the brain and spinal cord but has no transmission activity; the dendrite is the locus of the synapse.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:45:59', '2021-01-20 22:45:59'),
(1359, 28, 1, 'The one that provides temporary protection and care to children requiring emergency reception as a result of fortuitous events, abandonment by parents, dangerous condition of neglect or cruelty in the home, being without the adult care because of crisis in the family or a court order holding them as material witness is:', 'Shelter Care Institution', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:45:59', '2021-01-20 22:45:59'),
(1360, 29, 1, 'The nurse assesses a K+ level of 6.2 mEq/L and becomes alert for the associated sign of (select all that apply):\r\n1.	pain on movement.\r\n2.	contractions of the hands.\r\n3.	twitching of muscles.\r\n4.	lethargy.\r\n5.	trembling of limbs.', 'Increased levels of K+ cause twitching and tremor related to the altered depolarization that provides for smooth organized function.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:46:58', '2021-01-20 22:46:58'),
(1361, 29, 1, 'The nurse organizes the plan of care with regard to normal brain alterations associated with age, which are (select all that apply):\r\n1.	decrease in brain weight.\r\n2.	pigmentation of brain with lipofuscin.\r\n3.	present of amyloid.\r\n4.	tiny clot formation.\r\n5.	tangled nerve fibers.', 'All listed are expected changes that affect the older adult’s neurologic function except for tiny clot formations, which are pathologic changes.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:47:53', '2021-01-20 22:47:53'),
(1362, 29, 1, 'The nurse assessing the level of consciousness in a patient will do the following (arrange in order, from the simplest to the most complex):\r\n1.	Apply pressure to the nailbed.\r\n2.	Shake patient.\r\n3.	Touch the patient.\r\n4.	Call the patient’s name.\r\n5.	Approach the patient.', 'The assessment begins with simply approaching the patient and progresses to imposing painful stimuli.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:48:51', '2021-01-20 22:48:51'),
(1363, 29, 1, 'The nurse conducting a Romberg test will ask the patient to (arrange in correct sequence):\r\n1.	touch his or her nose with the index finger with the eyes open\r\n2.	stand with eyes closed\r\n3.	touch his or her nose with the index finger with the eyes closed\r\n4.	touch his or her fingertip to nurse’s fingertip\r\n5.	pat the knees with the palms and then the back of the hands rapidly', 'These simple exercises help assess balance and perception.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:50:12', '2021-01-20 22:50:12'),
(1364, 31, 1, 'A postoperative patient is complaining of incisional pain. An order has been given for morphine every 4 to 6 hours PRN. The first assessment by the nurse should be to:', 'Verifying the time of the last dose decreases the risk of a dose of medication being given too soon.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:52:17', '2021-01-20 22:52:17'),
(1365, 31, 1, 'The nurse is admitting a patient who is scheduled for a hysterectomy. Malignant hyperthermia is a potential postoperative complication. In gathering information on the patient’s medical history, the nurse should ask:', 'Malignant hyperthermia is a life-threatening complication that occurs in response to certain drugs. Susceptibility to this response is inherited.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:52:53', '2021-01-20 22:52:53'),
(1366, 31, 1, 'A patient who had a hysterectomy yesterday has been NPO. The physician has now ordered the patient’s diet to be clear liquids. Before administering the diet, the nurse should check for:', 'Absence of bowel sounds would contraindicate a diet.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:53:42', '2021-01-20 22:53:42'),
(1367, 31, 1, 'The technique the nurse should use to change a postoperative dressing is:', 'Aseptic technique is important to reduce the risk of infection.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:54:16', '2021-01-20 22:54:16'),
(1368, 31, 1, 'The nurse is caring for the postoperative patient who has had spinal anesthesia. The nurse would place highest priority on reporting which of these assessments?', 'One complication of spinal anesthesia is postspinal headache. It is caused by the leaking of cerebrospinal fluid at the puncture site.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:54:40', '2021-01-20 22:54:40'),
(1369, 31, 1, 'The nurse is caring for a postoperative patient. To best prevent deep vein thrombosis (DVT) in this patient, the nurse plans to diligently ensure that the patient:', 'DVT is best prevented by early and frequent ambulation of the patient.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:55:13', '2021-01-20 22:55:13'),
(1370, 31, 1, 'During the nurse’s preoperative assessment, the nurse notices that the patient is extremely anxious. The patient’s blood pressure is 142/92 mm Hg, heart rate is 104 per minute, and respirations are 34. The nurse should:', 'Extreme fear is associated with surgical complications. Sometimes, surgery is postponed until anxiety is reduced.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:56:03', '2021-01-20 22:56:03'),
(1371, 31, 1, 'The nurse is performing a postoperative assessment on a patient who has just returned from a hernia repair. The patient’s blood pressure is 90/60 mm Hg and apical pulse is 102. The nurse’s first action would be to:', 'A decrease in blood pressure and tachycardia could indicate postoperative bleeding. The first action of the nurse should be to check the dressing and then report to the RN', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:56:37', '2021-01-20 22:56:37'),
(1372, 31, 1, 'The postoperative patient who has no previous medical conditions is difficult to arouse when transferred to the surgical unit from the postanesthesia care unit. The nurse monitors the pulse oximeter and gets a reading of 85%. The nurse’s next action should be to:', 'If the pulse oximeter reading is less than 90%, the patient should be aroused and encouraged to take deep breaths. The patient’s respirations may not be adequate as a result of the effects of anesthesia.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:57:11', '2021-01-20 22:57:11'),
(1373, 31, 1, 'The nurse has completed giving discharge instructions to the patient after a hernia repair. The nurse would determine that the patient understands the instructions if he verbalizes that he will:', 'The patient should report any signs and symptoms of infection (fever, redness, swelling, or pain).', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:57:42', '2021-01-20 22:57:42'),
(1374, 31, 1, 'The nurse should include the proper use of an incentive spirometer in teaching for a preoperative patient. Postoperative monitoring of this patient would reveal that the incentive spirometry has been effective if the patient has:', 'An incentive spirometer is used to promote lung expansion, which opens airways, reduces atelectasis, and stimulates coughing to clear secretions.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:58:11', '2021-01-20 22:58:11'),
(1375, 31, 1, 'The suprapubic area of a postoperative patient is distended. The patient states that he has not voided since surgery about 9 hours ago. The nurse’s first action would be to:', 'The patient should be encouraged to try to void in a “natural” position before other measures are taken.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:58:38', '2021-01-20 22:58:38'),
(1376, 31, 1, 'Postoperative instructions must be modified for a patient with an intraocular lens implant. The nurse modifies postoperative care from that given most general surgery patients as follows:', 'There are a few instances in which coughing is contraindicated. They include surgeries for hernias, cataracts, and brain surgery.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:59:08', '2021-01-20 22:59:08'),
(1377, 31, 1, 'When obtaining the patient’s signature on the operative consent form, the patient seems confused about the procedure to be performed. The appropriate response by the nurse is to:', 'The patient may not understand some of the medical terms used by the physician and the nurse may be able to explain them. If the patient still needs further information, notify the physician. It is the physician’s responsibility to explain the procedure and risks to the patient', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 22:59:43', '2021-01-20 22:59:43'),
(1378, 31, 1, 'The nurse is doing an assessment of a patient who has returned from a cardiac catheterization and had conscious sedation. The nurse should report which of the following findings?', 'Conscious sedation uses intravenous drugs to reduce pain intensity or awareness without loss of reflexes. A complication may be excessive sedation approaching that of general anesthesia. The patient should be easily aroused.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 23:00:08', '2021-01-20 23:00:08'),
(1379, 31, 1, 'A patient diagnosed with colon cancer is being prepared for palliative surgery to correct an intestinal obstruction. The nurse understands that palliative surgery is:', 'Palliative surgery is done only to relieve symptoms or improve function. It is not curative', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 23:01:32', '2021-01-20 23:01:32'),
(1380, 31, 1, 'During the preoperative assessment, it is most important that the nurse ask the patient for information about:', 'If an emergency should arise, any allergies can be determined promptly. Knowledge of the patient’s medications can enable you to anticipate possible drug interactions. Past medical conditions may increase surgical risks or require special attention in the perioperative period.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 23:02:07', '2021-01-20 23:02:07'),
(1381, 30, 1, 'According to philosophers, which of the following theories covers the police ethical code and law enforcement code of ethics?', 'Normative', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-20 23:55:31', '2021-01-20 23:55:31'),
