INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `lesson_id`, `enabled`, `question_text`, `justification`, `difficulty`, `time`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1471, 32, 1, 'Your patient who is being treated for hyperparathyroidism is receiving calcitonin. The action of this hormone is to:', 'Calcitonin is a thyroid hormone that counteracts the effects of the parathormone released by the parathyroid gland. In this case, the parathormone is excessive.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:24:39', '2021-01-21 16:24:39'),
(1472, 30, 1, 'All of these are professional conduct and ethical standard except?', 'Standards police professionalism', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:25:15', '2021-01-21 16:25:15'),
(1473, 32, 1, 'An appropriate nursing diagnosis for a patient with hyperparathyroidism would be:', 'Excessive calcium in the bloodstream leads to formation of calcium stones in the urinary system.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:25:16', '2021-01-21 16:25:16'),
(1474, 32, 1, 'An appropriate nursing diagnosis for a patient with hypoparathyroidism would be:', 'A decreased amount of calcium in the bloodstream decreases the contractility of the heart.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:25:48', '2021-01-21 16:25:48'),
(1475, 32, 1, 'The nurse recommends the use of salt that is iodized because iodized salt:', 'Iodine is needed to convert thyroid hormones. Without it, the thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) continues to send the message to the thyroid gland to increase production of thyroid hormones.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:26:18', '2021-01-21 16:26:18'),
(1476, 30, 1, 'Which of the following is the police officer creed and stand on basic issues?', 'PNP image', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:26:48', '2021-01-21 16:26:48'),
(1477, 30, 1, 'All of these are police professional conduct except?', 'secrecy discipline', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:27:23', '2021-01-21 16:27:23'),
(1478, 32, 1, 'The patient who has hypothyroidism can live a full and normal life if he is:', 'Hormones can adequately and effectively replace the missing thyroid hormone.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:27:39', '2021-01-21 16:27:39'),
(1479, 32, 1, 'The nurse explains to the patient that the presurgical protocol of antithyroid drugs is given to (select all that apply):\r\n1.	decrease the level of hormone in the blood prior to surgery\r\n2.	help reduce the risk of hemorrhage during surgery\r\n3.	decrease the threat of thyroid storm\r\n4.	reduce exophthalmia\r\n5.	increase weight', 'The antithyroid medication will do all of the above except for increasing weight in a hyperthyroid patient.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:28:31', '2021-01-21 16:28:31'),
(1480, 32, 1, 'The nurse caring for a hyperthyroid patient would include in the nursing care plan implementations for (select all that apply):\r\n1.	decreasing weight\r\n2.	provision of a cool environment\r\n3.	eye care\r\n4.	nutritional support\r\n5.	prevention of diarrhea', 'A patient with hyperthyroidism does not need to lose weight, but to gain it. All other options are appropriate concerns for such a patient.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:29:20', '2021-01-21 16:29:20'),
(1481, 32, 1, 'The nurse makes a list of symptoms that the patient who is on methimazole (Tapazole), a thionamide drug, should report, which list includes (select all that apply):\r\n1.	becoming pregnant\r\n2.	jaundice\r\n3.	blood in the stool\r\n4.	rash\r\n5.	abdominal pain', 'All the side effects and concerns are those that the patient should report.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:30:01', '2021-01-21 16:30:01'),
(1482, 30, 1, 'All of these are police professional conduct except?', 'secrecy discipline', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:37:16', '2021-01-21 16:37:16'),
(1483, 30, 1, 'In police code covenant, police  service is:', 'honorable calling', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:38:16', '2021-01-21 16:38:16'),
(1484, 33, 1, 'A Cromolyn sodium (Intal) inhaler is prescribed to a client with asthma. The healthcare provider gives health teachings regarding the adverse effects of this drug. The nurse tells the client that which undesirable effect is associated with this medication?', 'Cromolyn Sodium (Intal) is used to prevent asthma attacks in people with bronchial asthma. Undesirable side effects associated with the use of inhaler is wheezing, cough, nasal congestion, bronchospasm and throat irritation.\r\n- Options B, C, and D, are not related to the medication.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:39:37', '2021-01-21 16:39:37'),
(1485, 30, 1, 'The virtue that regulates those actions which society may just require of the individual for common good is called?', 'Distributive justice', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:40:42', '2021-01-21 16:40:42'),
(1486, 33, 1, 'A client is prescribed with Guaifenesin (Mucinex). The nurse identifies that the patient fully understands the proper administration of this drug if the patient states that he or she will:', 'Guaifenesin is an expectorant. Drink extra fluids to help loosen the congestion and lubricate the throat while taking this medication.\r\n- Option B: The medication does not have to be taken with meals.\r\n- Option C: Additional doses should not be taken without the prescription of the doctor.\r\n- Option D: Fluids are needed to loosen the secretions.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:40:43', '2021-01-21 16:40:43'),
(1487, 30, 1, 'The relation which consist of the peace officers duties towards courts when appearing as a witness is known as:', 'judicial relation', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:41:49', '2021-01-21 16:41:49'),
(1488, 33, 1, 'A nursing practitioner is about to administer Albuterol (Ventolin HFA) 2 puff and Budesonide (Pulmicort Turbohaler) 2 puff by metered dose inhaler. The nurse plans to give by?', 'If two different inhaled medications are prescribed and one of the medications contains a corticosteroid, administer the bronchodilator (Albuterol) first and the corticosteroid (Budesonide) second. This will allow for the widening of the air passages by the bronchodilator, making the corticosteroids more effective.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:41:56', '2021-01-21 16:41:56'),
(1489, 33, 1, 'A nurse is about to administer Naloxone hydrochloride (Narcan) to a client with known narcotic drug toxicity. Which of the following apparatus should be readily available at the bedside?', 'While administering Narcan, resuscitation equipment, oxygen, mechanical ventilator should be readily available.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:42:29', '2021-01-21 16:42:29'),
(1490, 33, 1, 'A patient is receiving theophylline intravenously. After several dosages, the patient started to become restless and claims of palpitations. The nurse determines that the patient is suffering from theophylline toxicity in which of the following?', 'Theophylline toxicity is likely to occur when the serum level is higher than 20 mcg/ml. Early signs of toxicity include restlessness, nervousness, tachycardia, tremors and palpitations.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:43:07', '2021-01-21 16:43:07'),
(1491, 33, 1, 'A patient with a chronic obstructive pulmonary disease is prescribed with Ipratropium (Combivent). Upon reviewing the medical history of the patient, the nurse questions the prescription if which of the following is noted?', 'The client with a peanut allergy should not take ipratropium because the product contains soy lecithin, which is in the same plant family as peanuts.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:43:39', '2021-01-21 16:43:39'),
(1492, 33, 1, 'Montelukast (Singulair) is prescribed to a patient with asthma. During the medication therapy, which of the following laboratories should be monitored?', 'Montelukast (Singulair) is a leukotriene receptor and is used with caution in clients with impaired renal function. Alanine aminotransferase (ALT) and Aspartate aminotransferase (AST) should be monitor while taking this medication.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:44:24', '2021-01-21 16:44:24'),
(1493, 33, 1, 'The nurse is giving health instructions to a client receiving theophylline. The nurse instructs the latter to limit the intake of which of the following?', 'Theophylline is a methylxanthine bronchodilator. The nurse instructs the client to limit the intake of xanthine-containing foods such as chocolate, cola, and coffee.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:45:15', '2021-01-21 16:45:15'),
(1494, 33, 1, 'A nurse is providing health instructions to a client receiving Desloratadine (Clarinex). Which of the following statements made by the client will need further teaching?', 'This medicine should be taken with food or milk to minimize gastrointestinal upset.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:46:40', '2021-01-21 16:46:40'),
(1495, 30, 1, 'Reflect absences from duty for any reasons?', 'Awol', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:47:19', '2021-01-21 16:47:19'),
(1496, 33, 1, 'A pediatric patient with asthma has just received Omalizumab (Xolair). The nurse correctly identifies that the former might be suffering a life-threatening effect in which of the following?', 'Omalizumab (Xolair) Xolair is an anti-inflammatory that is used to treat moderate to severe asthma that is caused by allergies. An anaphylactic reaction may happen such as flushing, rash, wheezing or swelling of the face, lips or tongue.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:47:49', '2021-01-21 16:47:49'),
(1497, 30, 1, 'An appropriate type of dress and standard of good grooming is required in very position is an example of :', 'Grooming and dress', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:48:13', '2021-01-21 16:48:13'),
(1498, 30, 1, 'Refers to all public contact made through personal or telephone conservation, correspondence, and day-to- day appearance before the public. This is', 'Public contact', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:48:52', '2021-01-21 16:48:52'),
(1499, 33, 1, 'A patient with influenza is prescribed with an antiviral drug. The nurse determines that the patient indicates an understanding of the treatment if he states which of the following?', 'Antiviral drugs are taken exactly as prescribed\r\nOption: Antiviral drugs do not prevent the spread of influenza and patients are still contagious for up to two days after the start of the therapy.\r\nOption: The durations for the medications are followed until the last day of the treatment.\r\nOption: Side effects such as dizziness and drowsiness will alert the client to be careful resuming their daily activities.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:49:11', '2021-01-21 16:49:11'),
(1500, 30, 1, 'It is a decision that very employee’s makes depending upon the degree of responsibility assigned in his position. This is', 'decision making', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:49:49', '2021-01-21 16:49:49'),
(1501, 33, 1, 'A patient is to begin taking Rifampin (Rifadin). The nurse correctly teaches the him this medication:', 'ifampin causes red-orange discolorations of bodily secretions such as sweat, urine, tears, and feces.\r\nOption  The client should not stop the therapy unless with a doctor’s advice.\r\nOption: The medication is taken on an empty stomach.\r\nOption: Doses are not to be doubled or skipped.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:50:07', '2021-01-21 16:50:07'),
(1502, 30, 1, 'It is the wise use of judgment. this is', 'Discretion', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:50:30', '2021-01-21 16:50:30'),
