(1509, 33, 1, 'A nurse is caring for a patient who is starting a long-term therapy of isoniazid (INH). The nurse plans to instruct the latter to which of the following?', 'Isoniazid (INH) is hepatotoxic hence the client is instructed to report signs of jaundice (Yellowish of skin or the sclera).\r\nOption: Vitamin B6 can help in preventing peripheral neuritis.\r\nOption: Tuna which contains tyramine causes a reaction characterized by redness, flushing, sweating, itching of the skin while taking INH.\r\nOption: Avoid alcohol because the medication is hepatotoxic.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:54:24', '2021-01-21 16:54:24'),
(1510, 30, 1, 'All PNP members must undergo physical fitness activities and should  always maintain their waistline  at what measurement:', 'Smaller than the size of his chest and in conformity with the standard set forth by the organization', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:55:26', '2021-01-21 16:55:26'),
(1511, 33, 1, 'A patient has been taking isoniazid (INH). The patient went to the health care facility with complaints of numbness and tingling sensation in the extremities. The nurse determines that the patient is most likely suffering from?', 'Isoniazid (INH) causes peripheral neuritis characterized by numbness, tingling, and paresthesias in the extremities.\r\nOption: Guillain-Barre syndrome is a rare condition in which your immune system attacks your nerves, leading to muscle weakness and even paralysis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:55:52', '2021-01-21 16:55:52'),
(1512, 30, 1, 'In police code covenant, police service is.', 'honorable calling', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:55:58', '2021-01-21 16:55:58'),
(1513, 30, 1, 'An ounce of loyalty is worth a pound of…', 'Cleverness', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:56:33', '2021-01-21 16:56:33'),
(1514, 30, 1, 'If an officer vilify, condemn and eternally disparage; he should', 'resign his position', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:57:03', '2021-01-21 16:57:03'),
(1515, 30, 1, 'A Filipino policeman is not a friend of the people but a protector of the people?', 'False', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:57:33', '2021-01-21 16:57:33'),
(1516, 33, 1, 'A nurse is monitoring a patient receiving an Ethambutol (Myambutol) for adverse effects. The nurse determines that the patient is experiencing a side effect of the medication, in which of the following?', 'Ethambutol (Myambutol) causes optic neuritis characterized by decreased visual acuity and the ability to distinguish between the color red from green.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:57:46', '2021-01-21 16:57:46'),
