(1518, 33, 1, 'A patient diagnosed with tuberculosis is receiving Ethambutol (Myambutol). All of which are laboratories to be examined, except? ', 'Triglyceride level is not monitored during the treatment.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:58:26', '2021-01-21 16:58:26'),
(1519, 30, 1, 'The binding spirit the enhance team work and cooperation between all PNP member in the organization', 'Camaraderie', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:58:30', '2021-01-21 16:58:30'),
(1520, 33, 1, 'A nurse is giving instructions to a patient receiving Pyrazinamide. Which of the following is not true regarding this medication? ', 'Patients taking pyrazinamide decreases the effects of allopurinol, colchicine, probenecid, and sulfinpyrazone.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:59:01', '2021-01-21 16:59:01'),
(1521, 30, 1, 'This is being conducted or done during the arrival and departure tendered to visiting dignitaries, VIP’s and other officials. This is', 'honor ceremony', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:59:06', '2021-01-21 16:59:06'),
(1522, 30, 1, 'The sacrifice their limbs and lives for their countrymen they are pledged to serve and our history itself attests that law enforcers should exemplified the tradition in defending the country. This is', 'valor', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:59:46', '2021-01-21 16:59:46'),
(1523, 33, 1, 'A patient is taking streptomycin. The nurse explains the nervous system side effects of this medication. The nurse correctly states that this medication causes damage in which cranial nerve? ', 'Nervous system side effects of streptomycin include eighth cranial nerve toxicity, which typically affects the vestibular system (Clumsiness, dizziness, unsteadiness), but may also affect the auditory component (Ringing in the ear, loss of hearing).', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 16:59:56', '2021-01-21 16:59:56'),
(1524, 33, 1, 'All of which are examples of antiviral influenza medications except? ', 'Ethionamide (Trecator) is an antibiotic used in the treatment of tuberculosis.', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 17:00:55', '2021-01-21 17:00:55'),
(1525, 33, 1, 'Rifabutin (Mycobutin) is prescribed to a client with active Mycobacterium avium complex disease and tuberculosis. The nurse determines that the client is experiencing side effects in which of the following, except? ', 'Tingling and numbness of the fingers is more associated with the use of isoniazid (INH).', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 17:01:40', '2021-01-21 17:01:40'),
(1526, 30, 1, 'Matters pertaining to assignment, awards, training and promotion of all PNP members that inhibit themselves is an example of', 'political patronage', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 17:02:05', '2021-01-21 17:02:05'),
(1527, 30, 1, 'Code of honor facility or overtly observed by law enforcement officer upholding both the spirit and letter of the law fulfilling the mission statement police agency. What is this code?', 'Code of conduct', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 17:03:15', '2021-01-21 17:03:15'),
(1528, 30, 1, 'The branch of moral science which treats of the obligation which a member of a profession owes to the public, to his profession, to his brethren, and to his clients is?', 'professional ethics', 'easy', 30, '2021-01-21 17:05:44', '2021-01-21 17:05:44'),
